obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (9948)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9948&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1)This Act may be called the Mines and Minerals ^1(Development and Regulation) Act, 1957.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2 as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 1999, s. 3, for "(Regulation and Development)" (w.e.f. 18-12-1999).`
  line
  line `2. 1st June, 1958, vide notification No. G.S.R. 432, dated 29th May, 1958, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(i).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (9949)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Declaration as to expediency of Union Control.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9949&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `It is hereby declared that it is expedient in the`
  line `public interest that the Union should take under its control the regulation of mines and the development`
  line `of minerals to the extent hereinafter provided.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (9950)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9950&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,---`
  line
  line `^1[(a) "composite licence" means the prospecting licence-cum-mining lease which is a two stage`
  line `concession granted for the purpose of undertaking prospecting operations followed by mining`
  line `operations in a seamless manner;`
  line
  line `(aa) "dispatch" means the removal of minerals or mineral products from the leased area and`
  line `includes the consumption of minerals and mineral products within such leased area;`
  line
  line `^2[(aaa) "exploration licence" means a licence granted for undertaking reconnaissance operations`
  line `or prospecting operations or both in respect of minerals specified in the Seventh Schedule;]`
  line
  line `(ab) "Government company" shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in clause (45) of`
  line `section 2 of the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013);`
  line
  line `(ac) "leased area" means the area specified in the mining lease within which the mining`
  line `operations can be undertaken and includes the non-mineralized area required and approved for the`
  line `activities falling under the definition of "mine" as referred to in clause (i);`
  line
  line `(ad) "minerals" includes all minerals except minerals oils;`
  line
  line `(ae) "minerals concession" means either a reconnaissance permit, prospecting licence, minig`
  line `lease, composite licence ^2[, exploration licence] or a combination of any of these and the expression`
  line `"concession" shall be construed accordingly;]`
  line
  line `^3[(af) "mineral exchange" means an electronic trading platform or marketplace registered in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Act, where buyers and sellers of minerals, its concentrate or`
  line `its processed forms (including metals), transact, trade and enter into contract, including in`
  line derivatives;]
  line
  line `(b) "mineral oils" includes natural gas and petroleum;`
  line
  line `(c) "mining lease" means a lease granted for the purpose of undertaking mining operations, and`
  line `includes a sub-lease granted for such purpose;`
  line
  line `(d) "mining operations" means any operations undertaken for the purpose of winning any mineral;`
  line
  line `(e) "minor minerals" means building stones, gravel, ordinary clay, ordinary sand other than sand used`
  line `for prescribed purposes, and any other mineral which the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, declare to be a minor mineral;`
  line
  line `^4(ea) "notified minerals" means any mineral specified in the Fourth Schedule;]`
  line
  line `(f) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `^5[(fa) "production" or any derivative of the word "production" means the winning or raising of`
  line `mineral within the leased area for the purpose of processing or dispatch;]`
  line
  line `(g) "prospecting licence" means a licence granted for the purpose of undertaking prospecting`
  line operations;
  line
  line `^6* * * * *`
  line
  line `(h) "prospecting operations" means any operations undertaken for the purpose of exploring, locating`
  line `or proving mineral deposit ; ^7***`
  line
  line `^8[^9[(ha) "reconnaissance operations" means any operations undertaken for preliminary prospecting`
  line `of a mineral through regional, aerial, geophysical or geochemical surveys and geological mapping, and`
  line `include pitting, trenching, drilling and sub-surface excavation;]`
  line
  line `(hb) "reconnaissance permit" means a permit granted for the purpose of undertaking reconnaissance`
  line `operations; ^10***]`
  line
  line `^5[(hba) "Schedule" means the Schedules appended to the Act;]`
  line
  line `^4[(hc) "Special Court" means a Court of Session designated as Special Court under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 30B; and]`
  line
  line `(i) the expressions, "mine" and "owner", have the meaning assigned to them in the Mines Act, 1952`
  line `(35 of 1952).`
  line
  line `^5[Explanation.--- For the purpose of this clause, ---`
  line
  line `(i) a mine continues to be a mine till exhaustion of its mineable mineral reserve and a mine may`
  line `have different owners during different times from the grant of first mining lease till exhaustion of`
  line `such mineable mineral reserve;`
  line
  line `(ii) the expression "mineral reserve" means the economically minearble part of a measured and`
  line `indicated mineral resource.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 16 of 2021, s. 3, for clause (a) and (aa) (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 16 of 2023, s. 2 (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 28 of 2025, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-9-2025).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 10 of 2015, s. 2 (w.e.f. 12-1-2015).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 16 of 2021, s. 3 (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line
  line `6. Cl. (ga) omitted by s. 3, ibid (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line
  line `7. The word "and" omitted by Act 38 of 1999, s. 4 (w.e.f. 18-12-1999).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 18-12-1999).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by Act 16 of 2023, s. 2, for clause (ha) (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `10. The word "and" omitted by Act 10 of 2015, s. 2 (w.e.f. 12-1-2015).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (9951)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Prospecting or mining operations to be under licence or lease.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9951&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `^1[No person shall`
  line `undertake any reconnaissance, prospecting or mining operations in any area, except under and in`
  line `accordance with the terms and conditions of a reconnaissance permit or of a prospecting licence ^2[or of a`
  line `exploration licence] or, as the case may be, of a mining lease, granted under this Act and the rules made`
  line `thereunder]:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall affect any prospecting or mining operations undertaken in any`
  line `area in accordance with terms and conditions of a prospecting licence ^2[or of a exploration licence], mining lease`
  line `granted before the commencement of this Act which is in force at such commencement:`
  line
  line `^3[Provided further that nothing in this sub-section shall apply to any prospecting operations`
  line `undertaken by the Geological Survey of India, the Indian Bureau of Mines, ^4[the Atomic Minerals`
  line `Directorate for Exploration and Research] of the Department of Atomic Energy of the Central`
  line `Government, the Directorates of Mining and Geology of any State Government (by whatever name`
  line `called), and the Mineral Exploration Corporation Limited., a Government company within the meaning`
  line `of ^5[clause (45) of section 2 of the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013), and any ^6[other entities including`
  line `private entities that may be notified for this purpose, subject to such conditions as may be specified by`
  line `the Central Government]]:]`
  line
  line `^7[Provided also that nothing in this sub-section shall apply to any mining lease (whether called`
  line `mining lease mining concession or by any other name) in force immediately before the commencement`
  line `of this Act in the Union territory of Goa, Daman and Diu.]`
  line
  line `^8[(1A) No person shall transport or store or cause to be transported or stored any mineral otherwise`
  line `than in accordance with the provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder.]`
  line
  line `(2) ^9[No ^10[mineral concession]] shall be granted otherwise than in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `this Act and the rules made thereunder.`
  line
  line `^7[(3)Any State Government may, after prior consultation with the Central Government and in`
  line `accordance with the rule made under section 18, ^11[undertake reconnaissance, prospecting or mining`
  line `operations with respect to any mineral specified in the First Schedule in any area within that State which`
  line `is not already held under any ^10[mineral concession]].]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 1999, s. 5, for certain words (w.e.f. 18-12-1999).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 16 of 2023, s. 3 (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 37 of 1986, s. 2 (w.e.f. 10-2-1987).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 38 of 1999, s. 5, for "the Atomic Minerals Division" (w.e.f. 18-12-1999).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 10 of 2015, s. 3, for "section 617 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956)" (w.e.f. 12-1-2015).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 16 of 2021, s. 4, for certain words (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 16 of 1987, s. 14 (w.e.f. 1-10-1963).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by Act 38 of 1999, s. 5 (w.e.f. 18-12-1999).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., "No prospecting licence or mining lease" (w.e.f. 18-12-1999).`
  line
  line `10. Subs. by Act 16 of 2021, s. 2, for "reconnaissance permit, prospecting licence or mining lease" (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line
  line `11. Subs. by Act 38 of 1999, s. 5, for certain words (w.e.f. 18-12-1999).`
obj_root_law_sections_4_a:
  sectionId (9952)
  sectionNo 4A
  orderNo 5
  title `Termination of prospecting licences, exploration licences or mining leases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9952&sectionno=4A&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_4_a_content:
  string
  line ^1[
  line `^2[4A.Termination of prospecting licences, exploration licences or mining leases.]--- (1) Where`
  line `the Central Government, after consultation with the State Government, is of opinion that it is expedient`
  line `in the interest of regulation of mines and mineral development, preservation of natural environment,`
  line `control of floods, prevention of pollution, or to avoid danger to public health or communications or to`
  line `ensure safety of buildings, monuments or other structures or for conservation of mineral resources or for`
  line `maintaining safety in the mines or for such other purposes, as the Central Government may deem fit, it`
  line `may request the State Government to make a premature termination of a ^3[prospecting licence or`
  line `exploration licence] or mining lease in respect of any mineral other than a minor mineral in any area or`
  line `part thereof, and, on receipt of such request, the State Government shall make an order making a`
  line `premature termination of such ^3[prospecting licence or exploration licence] or mining lease with respect`
  line `to the area or any part thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the State Government ^4*** is of opinion that it is expedient in the interest of regulation`
  line `of mines and mineral development, preservation of natural environment, control of floods, prevention of`
  line `pollution or to avoid danger to public health or communications or to ensure safety of buildings,`
  line `monuments or other structures or for such other purposes, as the State Government may deem fit, it may,`
  line `by an order, in respect of any minor mineral, make premature termination of prospecting licence or`
  line `mining lease with respect to the area or any part thereof covered by such licence or lease.`
  line
  line `^5[* * * * *]`
  line
  line `(3) No order making a premature termination of a prospecting licence ^6[or exploration licence] or`
  line `mining lease shall be, made except after giving the holder of the licence or lease a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the holder of a mining lease fails to undertake ^6[production and dispatch] for a period of`
  line `^8[two years] after the date of execution of the lease or having commenced ^7[production and dispatch],`
  line `has discontinued the same for a period of ^8[two years], the lease shall lapse on the expiry of the period of`
  line `^8[two years] from the date of execution of the lease or, as the case may be, discontinuance of the`
  line `^7[production and dispatch]:`
  line
  line `^9[Provided that the State Government may, on an application made by the holder of such lease before`
  line `it lapses and on being satisfied that it shall not be possible for the holder of the lease to undertake`
  line `production and dispatch or to continue such production and dispatch for reasons beyond his control, make`
  line `anorder, within a period of three months from the date of receipt of such application,to extend the period of`
  line `two years by a further period not exceeding one year andsuch extension shall not be granted for more than`
  line `once during the entire period of lease:`
  line
  line `Provided further that such lease shall lapse on failure to undertake production and dispatch or having`
  line `commenced the production and dispatch fails to continue the same before the end of such extended`
  line period].]
obj_root_law_sections_4_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 37 of 1986, s. 3, for section 4A (w.e.f. 10-2-1987).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 16 of 2023, s. 4, for the marginal heading (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for prospecting license (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `4. The words , after consultation with the Central Government, omitted by Act 25 of 1994, s. 2 (w.e.f. 25-1-1994).`
  line
  line `5. Proviso omitted by Act 38 of 1999, s. 6 (w.e.f. 18-12-1999).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 16 of 2023, s. 4 (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 16 of 2021, s. 5, for mining operations (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 25 of 1994, s. 2, for one year (w.e.f. 25-1-1994).`
  line
  line `9. The provisos first, second, third and fourth subs. by Act 16 of 2021, s. 5 (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_4_b:
  sectionId (49829)
  sectionNo 4B
  orderNo 6
  title `Conditions for efficiency in production.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 2020, s. 2 (w.e.f. 10-1-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=49829&sectionno=4B&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_4_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[4B. Conditions for efficiency in production-- Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `section 4A, the Central Government may, in the interest of maintaining sustained production of minerals`
  line `in the country, prescribe such conditions as may be necessary for commencement and continuation of`
  line `production by the holders of mining leases who have acquired rights, approvals, clearances and the like`
  line `under section 8B.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (9953)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 7
  title `Restrictions on the grant of mineral concession.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9953&sectionno=5&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `^1[^2[5. Restrictions on the grant of mineral concession.]--- ^3[(1) A State Government shall not grant`
  line `a ^4[mineral concession] to any person unless such person--`
  line
  line `(a) is an Indian national, or company as defined in ^5[clause (20) of section 2 of the Companies`
  line `Act, 2013 (18 of 2013)]; and`
  line
  line `(b) satisfies such conditions as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `^6[Provided that in respect of any mineral specified in Part A and Part B of the First Schedule,`
  line `no ^4[mineral concession] shall be granted except with the`
  line `previous approval of the Central Government.]`
  line
  line `^7[Provided further that the previous approval of the Central Government shall not be required`
  line `for grant of ^2[mineral concession] in respect of the minerals specified in Part A of the First`
  line `Schedule, where,---`
  line
  line `(i) an allocation order has been issued by the Central Government under section 11A; or`
  line
  line `(ii) a notification of reservation of area has been issued by the Central Government or the`
  line `State Government under sub-section (1A) or sub-section (2) of section 17A; or`
  line
  line `(iii) a vesting order or an allotment order has been issued by the Central Government under the`
  line `provisions of the Coal Mines (Special Provisions) Act, 2015 (11 of 2015).]`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of this sub-section, a person shall be deemed to be an Indian`
  line national,---
  line
  line `(a) in the case of a firm or other association of individuals, only if all the members of the firm or`
  line `members of the association are citizens of India; and`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of an individual, only if he is a citizen of India.]`
  line
  line `^8[Provided also that the composite licence or mining lease shall not be granted for an area to any`
  line `person other than the Government, Government company or corporation, in respect of any minerals`
  line `specified in Part B of the First Schedule where the grade of such mineral in such area is equal to or`
  line `above such threshold value as may be notified by the Central Government.]`
  line
  line `(2) No mining lease shall be granted by the State Government unless it is satisfied that--`
  line
  line `^9[(a) there is evidence to show the existence of mineral contents in the area for which the`
  line `application for a mining lease has been made in accordance with such parameters as may be`
  line `prescribed for this purpose by the Central Government;]`
  line
  line `(b) there is a mining plan duly approved by the Central Government, or by the State`
  line `Government, in respect of such category of mines as may be specified by the Central Government,`
  line `for the development of mineral deposits in the area concerned:]`
  line
  line `^10[Provided that a mining lease may be granted upon the filing of a mining plan in accordance`
  line `with a system established by the State Government for preparation, certification, and monitoring of`
  line `such plan, with the approval of the Central Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 37 of 1986, s. 4, for section 5 (w.e.f. 10-2-1987).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 16 of 2023, s. 5, for the marginal heading (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 25 of 1994, s. 3, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 25-1-1994).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 16 of 2021, s. 2, "reconnaissance permit, prospecting licence or mining lease" (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 10 of 2015, s. 5, for "sub-section (1) of section 3 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956)" (w.e.f. 12-1-2015).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for the proviso (w.e.f. 12-1-2015).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 2 of 2020, s. 3 (w.e.f. 10-1-2020).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by Act 16 of 2021, s. 6 (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by Act 10 of 2015, s. 5, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 12-1-2015).`
  line
  line `10. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 12-1-2015).`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (9954)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 8
  title `Maximum area for which mineral concession may be granted.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9954&sectionno=6&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `^1[ 6. Maximum area for which mineral concession may be granted.]--- ^2[(1) No person shall`
  line `acquire ^3*** in respect of any mineral or prescribed group of associated minerals ^4[in a State]--`
  line
  line `(a) one or more prospecting licences covering a total area of more than twenty-five square`
  line `kilometres; or`
  line
  line `^4[(aa) one or more reconnaissance permit covering a total area of ten thousand square kilometres:`
  line
  line `Provided that the area granted under a single reconnaissance permit shall not exceed five`
  line `thousand square kilometers; or]`
  line
  line `^5[(ab) one or more exploration licences covering a total area of more than five thousand square kilometres:`
  line
  line `Provided that the area granted under a single exploration licence shall not exceed one thousand square`
  line kilometres;]
  line
  line `(b) one or more mining leases covering a total area of more than ten square kilometres:`
  line
  line `^6[Provided that if the Central Government is of the opinion that in the interest of the`
  line `development of any mineral or industry, it is necessary so to do, it may, for reasons to be recorded in`
  line `writing, increase the aforesaid area limits in respect of prospecting licence or mining lease, in so far`
  line `as it pertains to any particular mineral, or to any specified category of deposits of such mineral, or to`
  line `any particular mineral located in any particular area.]`
  line
  line `^7[(c) any ^8[mineral concession] in respect of any area which is not compact or contiguous:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the State Government is of opinion that in the interests of the development of any`
  line `mineral, it is necessary so to do, it may, for reasons to be recorded in writing, permit any person to`
  line `acquire a ^8[mineral concession] in relation to any area which is not compact or contiguous.]]`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this section, a person acquiring by, or in the name of, another person a`
  line `^9[mineral concession] which is intended for himself shall be deemed to be acquiring it himself.`
  line
  line `^10[(3) For the purposes of determining the total area referred to in sub-section (1), the area held under`
  line a
  line `^9[mineral concession] by a person as a member of a co-operative society, company or other corporation`
  line `or a Hindu undivided family or a partner of a firm, shall be deducted from the area referred to in subsection (1) so that the sum total of the area held by such person, under a`
  line `^9[mineral concession], whether`
  line `as such member or partner, or individually, may not, in any case, exceed the total area specified in sub-section (1).]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
