obj_root_law_sections_6_a:
  sectionId (100318)
  sectionNo 6A
  orderNo 9
  title `Inclusion of contiguous area in the leased area or area under composite licence in case of deep-seated minerals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 28 of 2025, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-9-2025).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=100318&sectionno=6A&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[6A. Inclusion of contiguous area in the leased area or area under composite licence in case of`
  line `deep-seated minerals.--- (1) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 10,---`
  line
  line `(a) a holder of a mining lease of deep-seated mineral, may apply for a one-time extension of the`
  line `existing leased area to include therein a contiguous area not exceeding ten per cent. of the existing`
  line `leased area;`
  line
  line `(b) a holder of a composite licence in respect of deep-seated mineral, may apply for a one-time`
  line `extension of the area under the composite licence, to include therein a contiguous area not exceeding`
  line `thirty per cent. of the existing area under the licence.`
  line
  line `(2) Upon receipt of such application, the State Government may extend the existing leased area or the`
  line `area under composite licence, as the case may be, to include therein the contiguous area subject to such`
  line `terms and conditions and on payment of such additional amount as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this section, the expression "deep-seated minerals" means such`
  line `minerals which occur at a depth of more than two hundred meters from the surface of land with poor`
  line `surface manifestations.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (9955)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 10
  title `Periods for which prospecting licences may be granted or renewed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9955&sectionno=7&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `^1[7. Periods for which prospecting licences may be granted or renewed.--(1) The period for`
  line `which ^2[a reconnaissance permit or prospecting licence] may be granted shall not exceed three years.`
  line
  line `(2) A prospecting licence shall, if the State Government is satisfied that a longer period is required to`
  line `enable the licensee to complete prospecting operations be renewed for such period or periods as that`
  line `Government may specify:`
  line
  line `Provided that the total period for which a prospecting licence is granted does not exceed five years:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no prospecting licence granted in respect of ^3[a mineral included in Part A and`
  line `Part B to] the First Schedule shall be renewed except with the previous approval of the Central`
  line Government.]
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 1994, s. 4, for section 7 (w.e.f. 25-1-1994).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 38 of 1999, s. 9, for "a prospecting licence" (w.e.f. 18-12-1999).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 9, ibid., for "a mineral included in" (w.e.f. 18-12-1999).`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (9956)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 11
  title `Periods for which mining leases may be granted or renewed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9956&sectionno=8&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `^1[8. Periods for which mining leases may be granted or renewed.--(1) The provisions of this`
  line `section shall apply to minerals specified in Part A of the First Schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) The maximum period for which a mining lease may be granted shall not exceed thirty years:`
  line
  line `Provided that the minimum period for which any such mining lease may be granted shall not be less`
  line `than twenty years.`
  line
  line `(3) A mining lease may be renewed for a period not exceeding twenty years with the previous`
  line `approval of the Central Government.]`
  line
  line `^2[(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, in case of Government companies or`
  line `corporations, the period of mining leases including the existing mining leases, shall be such as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that the period of mining leases, other than the mining leases grantedthrough auction, shall`
  line `be extended on payment of such additional amount as specified in the Fifth Schedule:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette and for`
  line `reasons to be recorded in writing, amend the Fifth Schedule so as to modify the entries mentioned therein`
  line `in the said Schedule with effect from such date as may be specified in the said notification.`
  line
  line `(5) Any lessee may, where coal or lignite is used for captive purpose, sell suchcoal or lignite up to`
  line `fifty per cent. of the total coal or lignite produced in a year aftermeeting the requirement of the end use`
  line `plant linked with the mine in such manner as may be prescribed by the Central Government and on`
  line `payment of such additional amount as specified in the Sixth Schedule:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette and for the reasons to`
  line `be recorded in writing, increase the said percentage of coal orlignite that may be sold by a Government`
  line `company or corporation:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the sale of coal shall not be allowed from the coal mines allotted to a company`
  line `or corporation that has been awarded a power project on the basis of competitive bid for tariff (including`
  line `Ultra Mega Power Projects):`
  line
  line `Provided also that the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette and for`
  line `reasons to be recorded in writing, amend the Sixth Schedule so as tomodify the entries mentioned therein`
  line `with effect from such date as may be specified inthe said notification.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2015, s. 7, for section 8 (w.e.f. 12-1-2015).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 16 of 2021, s. 7 (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_8_a:
  sectionId (9957)
  sectionNo 8A
  orderNo 12
  title `Period of grant of a mining lease for minerals other than coal, lignite and atomic minerals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9957&sectionno=8A&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_8_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[8A. Period of grant of a mining lease for minerals other than coal, lignite and atomic`
  line `minerals.--(1) The provisions of this section shall apply to minerals other than those specified in Part A`
  line `and Part B of the First Schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) On and from the date of the commencement of the Mines and Minerals (Development and`
  line `Regulation) Amendment Act, 2015 (10 of 2015), all mining leases shall be granted for the period of fifty`
  line years.
  line
  line `(3) All mining leases granted before the commencement of the Mines and Minerals (Development`
  line `and Regulation) Amendment Act, 2015 (10 of 2015) shall be deemed to have been granted for a period`
  line `of fifty years.`
  line
  line `(4) On the expiry of the lease period, the lease shall be put up for auction as per the procedure`
  line `specified in this Act.`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that nothing contained in this section shall prevent the State Governments from taking an`
  line `advance action for auction of the mining lease before the expiry of the lease period.]`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (2), (3) and sub-section (4), the period of`
  line `lease granted before the date of commencement of the Mines and Minerals (Development and`
  line `Regulation) Amendment Act, 2015 (10 of 2015), where mineral is used for captive purpose, shall be`
  line `extended and be deemed to have been extended up to a period ending on the 31st March, 2030 with`
  line `effect from the date of expiry of the period of renewal last made or till the completion of renewal period,`
  line `if any, or a period of fifty years from the date of grant of such lease, whichever is later, subject to the`
  line `condition that all the terms and conditions of the lease have been complied with.`
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (2), (3) and sub-section (4), the period of`
  line `lease granted before the date of commencement of the Mines and Minerals (Development and`
  line `Regulation) Amendment Act, 2015 (10 of 2015), where mineral is used for other than captive purpose,`
  line `shall be extended and be deemed to have been extended up to a period ending on the 31st March, 2020`
  line `with effect from the date of expiry of the period of renewal last made or till the completion of renewal`
  line `period, if any, or a period of fifty years from the date of grant of such lease, whichever is later, subject to`
  line `the condition that all the terms and conditions of the lease have been complied with.`
  line
  line `(7) Any holder of a lease granted, where mineral is used for captive purpose, shall have the right of`
  line `first refusal at the time of auction held for such lease after the expiry of the lease period.`
  line
  line `^3[(7A) Any lessee may, where mineral is used for captive purpose, sell mineral ^4*** after meeting the requirement of the end use plant linked with the mine`
  line `in such manner as may be prescribed by the Central Government and on payment of such additional`
  line `amount as specified in the Sixth Schedule:`
  line
  line `^5[Provided that the State Government may permit sale of dumps which has been stacked up to such date as may`
  line `be specified by the Central Government in the leased area on payment of additional amount specified in the Sixth`
  line `Schedule:]`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette and for`
  line `reasons to be recorded in writing, amend the Sixth Schedule so as to modify the entries mentioned therein`
  line `with effect from such date as may be specified in the said notification.]`
  line
  line `(8) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, the period of mining leases, including`
  line `existing mining leases, of Government companies or corporations shall be such as may be prescribed by`
  line `the Central Government.`
  line
  line `^6[Provided that the period of mining leases, other than the mining leases granted through auction, shall`
  line `be extended on payment of such additional amount as specified in the Fifth Schedule:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette and for`
  line `reasons to be recorded in writing, amend the Fifth Schedule so as to modify the entries mentioned therein`
  line `with effect from such date as maybe specified in the said notification.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that all such Government companies`
  line `or corporations whose mining lease has been extended after the commencement of the Mines and Minerals (Development and Regulation) Amendment Act, 2015 (10 of 2015), shall also pay such additional`
  line `amount as specified in the Fifth Schedule for the mineral produced after the commencement of the Mines`
  line `and Minerals (Development and Regulation) Amendment Act, 2021.]`
  line
  line `(9) The provisions of this section, notwithstanding anything contained therein, shall not apply to a`
  line `mining lease granted before the date of commencement of the Mines and Minerals (Development and`
  line `Regulation) Amendment Act, 2015 (10 of 2015), for which renewal has been rejected, or which has been`
  line `determined, or lapsed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2015, s. 8 (w.e.f. 12-1-2015).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 2 of 2020, s. 4 (w.e.f. 10-1-2020).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 16 of 2021, s. 8 (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line
  line `4. The words "up to fifty per cent. of the total mineral produced in a year" omitted by Act 28 of 2025, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-9-2025).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 28 of 2025, s. 4, for the proviso (w.e.f. 1-9-2025).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 16 of 2021, s. 8 (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_8_b:
  sectionId (49830)
  sectionNo 8B
  orderNo 13
  title `Provisions for transfer of statutory clearances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_b_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 16 of 2021, s. 9, for section 8B (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=49830&sectionno=8B&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_8_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[8B. Provisions for period and transfer of statutory clearances.--- (1) Notwithstanding anything contained`
  line `in this Act or any other law for the time being in force, all valid rights, approvals, clearances, licences and the like`
  line `granted to a lessee in respect of a mine (other than those granted under the provisions of the Atomic Energy Act,`
  line `1962 (33 of 1962), and the rules made thereunder) shall continue to be valid even after expiry or termination of`
  line `lease and such rights, approvals, clearances, licences and the like shall be transferred to, and vested; subject to the`
  line `conditions provided under such laws; in the successful bidder of the mining lease selected through auction under this`
  line `Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that where on the expiry of such lease period, mining lease has not been executed pursuant to an`
  line `auction under provisions of sub-section (4) of section 8A, or lease executed pursuant to such auction has been`
  line `terminated within a period of one year from such auction, the State Government may, with the previous`
  line `approval of the Central Government, grant lease to a Government company or corporation for a period not`
  line `exceeding ten years or till selection of new lessee through auction, whichever is earlier and such Government`
  line `company or corporation shall be deemed to have acquired all valid rights, approvals, clearances, licences and the`
  line `like vested with the previous lessee:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the provisions of sub-section (1) of section 6 shall not apply where such mining lease is`
  line `granted to a Government company or corporation under the first proviso:`
  line
  line `Provided also that in case of atomic minerals having grade equal to or above the threshold value, all valid rights,`
  line `approvals, clearances, licences and the like in respectof expired or terminated mining leases shall be deemed to have`
  line `been transferred to, and vested in the Government company or corporation that has been subsequently granted the`
  line `mining lease for the said mine.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, it shall be lawful for the`
  line `new lessee to continue mining operations on the land till expiry or termination of mining lease granted to it, in which`
  line `mining operations were being carried out by the previous lessee.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (9958)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 14
  title `Royalties in respect of mining leases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9958&sectionno=9&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The holder of a mining lease granted before the`
  line `commencement of this Act shall, notwithstanding anything contained in the instrument of lease or in any`
  line `law in force at such commencement, pay royalty in respect of any ^1[mineral removed or consumed by`
  line `him or by his agent, manager, employee, contractor or sub-lessee] from the leased area after such`
  line `commencement, at the rate for the time being specified in the Second Schedule in respect of that mineral.`
  line
  line `(2)The holder of a mining lease granted on or after the commencement of this Act shall pay royalty`
  line `in respect of any ^1[mineral removed or consumed by him or by his agent, manager, employee, contractor`
  line `or sub-lessee] from the leased area at the rate for the time being specified in the Second Schedule in`
  line `respect of that mineral.`
  line
  line `^2[(2A) The holder of a mining lease, whether granted before or after the commencement of the Mines`
  line `and Minerals (Regulation and Development) Amendment Act, 1972 (56 of 1972) shall not be liable to`
  line `pay any royalty in respect of any coal consumed by a workman engaged in a colliery provided that such`
  line `consumption by the workman does not exceed one-third of a tonne per month.]`
  line
  line `(3)The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, amend the Second Schedule`
  line `so as to enhance or reduce the rate at which royalty shall be payable in respect of any mineral with effect`
  line `from such date as may be specified in the notification:`
  line
  line `^3[Provided that the Central Government shall not enhance the rate of royalty in respect of any`
  line `mineral more than once during any period of ^4[three years].]`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 56 of 1972, s. 4, for "mineral removed by him" (w.e.f. 12-9-1972).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 12-9-1972).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for the proviso (w.e.f. 12-9-1972).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 37 of 1986, s. 8, for "four years" (w.e.f. 10-2-1987).`
obj_root_law_sections_9_a:
  sectionId (9959)
  sectionNo 9A
  orderNo 15
  title `Dead rent to be paid by the lessee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9959&sectionno=9A&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_9_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[9A. Dead rent to be paid by the lessee.--(1) The holder of a mining lease, whether granted`
  line `before or after the commencement of the Mines and Minerals (Regulation and Development)`
  line `Amendment Act, 1972, shall notwithstanding anything contained in the instrument of lease or in any`
  line `other law for the lime being in force, pay to the State Government, every year, dead rent at such rate, as`
  line `may be specified, for the time being, in the Third Schedule, for all the areas included in the instrument of`
  line `lease:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the holder of such mining lease becomes liable, under section 9, to pay royalty`
  line `for any mineral removed or consumed by him or by his agent, manager, employee, contractor or sublessee`
  line `from the leased area, he shall be liable to pay either such royalty, or the dead rent in respect of that`
  line `area, whichever is greater.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, amend the Third Schedule`
  line `so as to enhance or reduce the rate at which the dead rent shall be payable in respect of any area covered`
  line `by a mining lease and such enhancement or reduction shall take effect from such date as may be`
  line `specified in the notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government shall not enhance the rate of the dead rent in respect of any`
  line `such area more than once during any period of ^2[three years].]`
obj_root_law_sections_9_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 56 of 1972, s. 5 (w.e.f. 12-9-1972).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 37 of 1986, s. 9, for "four years" (w.e.f. 10-2-1987).`
obj_root_law_sections_9_b:
  sectionId (9960)
  sectionNo 9B
  orderNo 16
  title `District Mineral Foundation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9960&sectionno=9B&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_9_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[9B. District Mineral Foundation.--(1) In any district affected by mining related operations, the`
  line `State Government shall, by notification, establish a trust, as a non-profit body, to be called the District`
  line `Mineral Foundation.`
  line
  line `(2) The object of the District Mineral Foundation shall be to work for the interest and benefit of`
  line `persons, and areas affected by mining related operations in such manner as may be prescribed by the`
  line `State Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The composition and functions of the District Mineral Foundation shall be such as may be`
  line `prescribed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that the Central Government may give directions regarding composition and utilisation`
  line `of fund by the District Mineral Foundation.]`
  line
  line `(4) The State Government while making rules under sub-sections (2) and (3) shall be guided by the`
  line `provisions contained in article 244 read with Fifth and Sixth Schedules to the Constitution relating to`
  line `administration of the Scheduled Areas and Tribal Areas and the Provisions of the Panchayats (Extension`
  line `to the Scheduled Areas) Act, 1996 (40 of 1996) and the Scheduled Tribes and Other Traditional Forest`
  line `Dwellers (Recognition of Forest Rights) Act, 2006 (2 of 2007).`
  line
  line `(5) The holder of a mining lease or a ^3[composite licence] granted on or after the date of`
  line `commencement of the Mines and Minerals (Development and Regulation) Amendment Act, 2015 ^4[,other than those covered under the provisions of sub-section (2) of section 10A], shall, in addition to the royalty, pay to the District Mineral Foundation of the district in which the mining operations are carried`
  line `on, an amount which is equivalent to such percentage of the royalty paid in terms of the Second`
  line `Schedule, not exceeding one-third of such royalty, as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(6) The holder of a mining lease granted before the date of commencement of the Mines and`
  line `Minerals (Development and Regulation) Amendment Act, 2015 ^5[and those covered under the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (2) of section 10A], shall, in addition to the royalty, pay to the District Mineral`
  line `Foundation of the district in which the mining operations are carried on, an amount not exceeding the`
  line `royalty paid in terms of the Second Schedule in such manner and subject to the categorisation of the`
  line `mining leases and the amounts payable by the various categories of lease holders, as may be prescribed`
  line `by the Central Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2015, s. 9 (w.e.f. 12-1-2015).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 16 of 2021, s. 10 (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 16 of 2021, s. 2, for "prospecting licence-cum-mining lease" (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 10, ibid. (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by s. 10, ibid (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_9_c:
  sectionId (9961)
  sectionNo 9C
  orderNo 17
  title `National Mineral Exploration and Development Trust.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9961&sectionno=9C&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_9_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[National Mineral Exploration and Development Trust.]--- (1) The Central Government`
  line `shall, by notification, establish a Trust, as a ^2[non-profit autonomous body], to be called the ^3[National`
  line `Mineral Exploration and Development Trust].`
  line
  line `^4[(2) The object of the Trust shall be to use the funds accrued to the Trust within India, including the`
  line `offshore areas, and outside India for the purposes of regional and detailed exploration and development`
  line `of mines and minerals in such manner as may be prescribed by the Central Government.]`
  line
  line `(3) The composition and functions of the Trust shall be such as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(4) The holder of a mining lease or a ^5[composite licence] shall pay to the Trust, a sum equivalent to`
  line `^6[three per cent.] of the royalty paid in terms of the Second Schedule, in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Central Government.]`
  line
  line `^7[(5) The entities specified and notified under sub-section (1) of section 4 shall be eligible for funding`
  line `under the ^3[National Mineral Exploration and Development Trust].]`
obj_root_law_sections_9_c_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 28 of 2025, s. 5, for marginal heading (w.e.f. 1-9-2025).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 16 of 2021, s. 11, for "non-profit body" (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 28 of 2025, s. 5, for "National Mineral Exploration Trust" (w.e.f. 1-9-2025).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 1-9-2025).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 16 of 2021, s. 2, for "prospecting licence-cum-mining lease" (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 28 of 2025, s. 5, for "two per cent." (w.e.f. 1-9-2025).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 16 of 2021, s. 11 (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (9962)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 18
  title `Application for mineral concession.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9962&sectionno=10&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `10. ^1[Application for mineral concession.]---(1) An application for ^2[a ^3[mineral concession]] in`
  line `respect of any land in which the minerals vest in the Government shall be made to the State Government`
  line `concerned in the prescribed form and shall be accompanied by the prescribed fee.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an application is received under sub-section (1), there shall be sent to the applicant an`
  line `acknowledgment of its receipt within the prescribed time and in the prescribed form.`
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of an application under this section, the State Government may, having regard to the`
  line `provisions of this Act and any rules made thereunder, grant or refuse to grant the ^4[permit, licence or`
  line lease].
  line
  line `^5[(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, no person shall be eligible to make an`
  line `application under this section unless--`
  line
  line `(a) he has been selected in accordance with the procedure specified under`
  line `^6[sections 10B, 10BA, 11,`
  line `11A, 11B or 11D];`
  line
  line `(b) he has been selected under the Coal Mines (Special) Provisions Act, 2015 (11 of 2015);`
  line or
  line
  line `(c) an area has been reserved in his favour under section 17A.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 16 of 2023 s. 8, for the marginal heading (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 38 of 1999, s. 11, for "a prospecting licence or a mining lease" (w.e.f. 18-12-1999).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 16 of 2021, s. 2, "reconnaissance permit, prospecting licence or mining lease" (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 38 of 1999, s. 11, for "licence or lease" (w.e.f. 18-12-1999).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 16 of 2021, s. 12 (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 16 of 2023, s. 8, for the words figures and letters "sections 10B, 11, 11A or the rules made under section 11B"`
  line `(w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_10_a:
  sectionId (9963)
  sectionNo 10A
  orderNo 19
  title `Rights of existing concession holders and applicants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9963&sectionno=10A&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[10A. Rights of existing concession holders and applicants.--(1) All applications received prior`
  line `to the date of commencement of the Mines and Minerals (Development and Regulation) Amendment`
  line `Act, 2015, shall become ineligible.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to sub-section (1), the following shall remain eligible on and from the date of`
  line `commencement of the Mines and Minerals (Development and Regulation) Amendment Act, 2015:--`
  line
  line `(a) applications received under section 11A of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) where before the commencement of the Mines and Minerals (Development and Regulation)`
  line `Amendment Act, 2015 a reconnaissance permit or prospecting licence has been granted in respect of`
  line `any land for any mineral, the permit holder or the licensee shall have a right for obtaining a`
  line `prospecting licence followed by a mining lease, or a mining lease, as the case may be, in respect of`
  line `that mineral in that land, if the State Government is satisfied that the permit holder or the licensee, as`
  line `the case may be,--`
  line
  line `(i) has undertaken reconnaissance operations or prospecting operations, as the case may be,`
  line `to establish the existence of mineral contents in such land in accordance with such parameters as`
  line `may be prescribed by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(ii) has not committed any breach of the terms and conditions of the reconnaissance permit`
  line `or the prospecting licence;`
  line
  line `(iii) has not become ineligible under the provisions of this Act; and`
  line
  line `(iv) has not failed to apply for grant of prospecting licence or mining lease, as the case may`
  line `be, within a period of three months after the expiry of reconnaissance permit or prospecting`
  line `licence, as the case may be, or within such further period not exceeding six months as may be`
  line `extended by the State Government;`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that for the cases covered under this clause including the pending cases, the right`
  line `to obtain a prospecting licence followed by a mining lease or a mining lease, as the case may be,`
  line `shall lapse on the date of commencement of the Mines and Minerals (Development and`
  line `Regulation) AmendmentAct, 2021:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the holder of a reconnaissance permit or prospecting licence whose`
  line `rights lapsed under the first proviso, shall be reimbursed the expenditure incurred towards`
  line `reconnaissance or prospecting operations in such manner as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line Government.]
  line
  line `(c) where the Central Government has communicated previous approval as required under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 5 for grant of a mining lease, or if a letter of intent (by whatever name`
  line `called) has been issued by the State Government to grant a mining lease, before the commencement`
  line `of the Mines and Minerals (Development and Regulation) Amendment Act, 2015, the mining lease shall be granted subject to fulfilment of the conditions of the previous approval or of the letter of`
  line `intent within a period of two years from the date of commencement of the said Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that in respect of any mineral specified in the First Schedule, no prospecting`
  line `licence or mining lease shall be granted under clause (b) of this subsection except with the`
  line `previous approval of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `^2[(d) in cases where right to obtain licence or lease has lapsed under, clauses (b) and (c), such`
  line `areas shall be put up for auction as per the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `Provided that in respect of the minerals specified in Part B of the First Schedule where the grade`
  line `of atomic mineral is equal to or greater than the thresholdvalue, the mineral concession for such areas`
  line `shall be granted in accordance with the rules made under section 11B.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2015, s. 10 (w.e.f. 12-1-2015).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 16 of 2021, s. 13 (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_10_b:
  sectionId (9964)
  sectionNo 10B
  orderNo 20
  title `Grant of mining lease in respect of notified minerals through auction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9964&sectionno=10B&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_10_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[10B. Grant of mining lease in respect of notified minerals through auction.--- ^2[(1) The`
  line `provisions of this section shall not apply to the,--`
  line
  line `(a) cases falling under section 17A;`
  line
  line `(b) minerals specified in Part A of the First Schedule;`
  line
  line `(c) minerals specified in Part B of the First Schedule where the grade of atomic mineral is equal to`
  line `or greater than such threshold value as maybe notified by the Central Government from time to time;`
  line or
  line
  line `(d) land in respect of which the minerals do not vest in the Government.]`
  line
  line `(2) Where there is inadequate evidence to show the existence of mineral contents of any notified`
  line `mineral in respect of any area, a State Government may, ^3*** grant a ^4[composite licence] for the said notified mineral in such area in accordance`
  line `with the procedure laid down in section 11.`
  line
  line `(3) In areas where the existence of mineral contents of any notified mineral is established in the`
  line `manner prescribed by the Central Government, the State Government shall notify such areas for grant of`
  line `mining leases for such notified mineral, the terms and conditions subject to which such mining leases`
  line `shall be granted, and any other relevant conditions, in such manner as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `^5[Provided that where the State Government has not notified such area for grant of mining lease after`
  line `establishment of existence of mineral contents of any mineral (whether notified mineral or otherwise), the`
  line `Central Government may require the State Government to notify such area within a period to be fixed in`
  line `consultation with the State Government and in cases where the notification is not issued within such`
  line `period, the Central Government may notify such area for grant of mining lease after the expiry of the`
  line `period so specified.]`
  line
  line `(4) For the purpose of granting a mining lease in respect of any notified mineral in such notified`
  line `area, the State Government shall select, through auction by a method of competitive bidding, including`
  line `e-auction, an applicant who fulfils the eligibility conditions as specified in this Act.`
  line
  line `^5[Provided that---`
  line
  line `(a) where the State Government has not successfully completed auction for the purpose of`
  line `granting a mining lease in respect of any mineral (whether notified mineral or otherwise) in such`
  line `notified area; or`
  line
  line `(b) upon completion of such auction, the mining lease or letter of intent for grant of mining lease`
  line `has been terminated or lapsed for any reason whatsoever,`
  line
  line `the Central Government may require the State Government to conduct and complete the auction or`
  line `re-auction process, as the case may be, within a period to be fixed in consultation with the State`
  line `Government and in cases where such auction or re-auction process is not completed within such`
  line `period, the Central Government may conduct auction for grant of mining lease for such area after the`
  line `expiry of the period so specified:`
  line
  line `Provided further that upon successful completion of the auction, the Central Government shall`
  line `intimate the details of the preferred bidder in the auction to the State Government and the State`
  line `Government shall grant mining lease for such area to such preferred bidder in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed by the CentralGovernment.]`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government shall prescribe the terms and conditions, and procedure, subject to`
  line `which the auction shall be conducted, including the bidding parameters for the selection, which may`
  line `include a share in the production of the mineral, or any payment linked to the royalty payable, or any`
  line `other relevant parameter, or any combination or modification of them.`
  line
  line `(6) Without prejudice to the generality of sub-section (5), the Central Government shall, if it is of the`
  line `opinion that it is necessary and expedient to do so, prescribe terms and conditions, procedure and`
  line `bidding parameters in respect of categories of minerals, size and area of mineral deposits and a State or`
  line `States, subject to which the auction shall be conducted:`
  line
  line `^6[Provided that no mine shall be reserved for captive purpose in the auction.]`
  line
  line `(7) The State Government shall grant a mining lease to an applicant selected in accordance with the`
  line `procedure laid down in this section in respect of such notified mineral in any notified area.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2015, s. 10 (w.e.f. 12-1-2015).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 16 of 2021, s. 14, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line
  line `3. The words ", after obtaining the previous approval of the Central Government," omitted by Act 28 of 2025, s. 6`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-9- 2025).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "prospecting licence-cum-mining lease" (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by s. 14, ibid. (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 16 of 2021, s. 14, for the proviso (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_10_ba:
  sectionId (77314)
  sectionNo 10BA
  orderNo 21
  title `Grant of exploration licence for minerals specified in Seventh Schedule through auction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_ba_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_ba_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=77314&sectionno=10BA&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_10_ba_content:
  string
  line `^1[^2[10BA. Grant of exploration licence for minerals specified in Seventh Schedule through auction.--- (1)`
  line `The provisions of this section shall not apply to---`
  line
  line `(a) the areas covered under section 17A;`
  line
  line `(b) the minerals specified in Part A of the First Schedule;`
  line
  line `(c) the minerals specified in Part B of the First Schedule where the grade of atomic mineral is equal to or`
  line `greater than such threshold value as may be notified by the Central Government from time to time;`
  line
  line `(d) any land in respect of which the minerals do not vest in the Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sections 10B and 11, an exploration licence may be granted in any`
  line `area by the State Government for the purpose of undertaking reconnaissance or prospecting operations or both in`
  line `respect of any mineral specified in the Seventh Schedule.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, and for reasons to be recorded in`
  line `writing, amend the Seventh Schedule so as to modify the entries therein with effect from such date as may be`
  line `specified in the said notification.`
  line
  line `(4) The State Government shall, after obtaining the previous approval of the Central Government, and in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed by the Central Government, notify the areas in which exploration licence shall be`
  line `granted, subject to such terms and conditions as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government may require the State Government to notify the area for grant of exploration`
  line `licence within such period as may be fixed in consultation with the State Government, and in case the State`
  line `Government does not notify the area within such period, the Central Government may, after the expiry of the`
  line `period so fixed, notify the area for grant of exploration licence.`
  line
  line `(6) The State Government shall, for the purpose of granting exploration licence through auction by method of`
  line `competitive bidding, including e-auction, select an applicant who fulfils the eligibility conditions as specified in`
  line `this Act and grant exploration licence to such applicant.`
  line
  line `(7) Where---`
  line
  line `(a) the State Government has not successfully completed auction for the grant of exploration licence; or`
  line
  line `(b) after completion of auction, the exploration licence or letter of intent for grant of exploration licence`
  line `has been terminated or lapsed for any reason whatsoever,`
  line `the Central Government may require the State Government to conduct and complete the auction or re-auction`
  line `process, as the case may be, within such period as may be fixed in consultation with the State Government, and in`
  line `cases where such auction or re-auction process is not completed within such period, the Central Government may,`
  line `after the expiry of the period so fixed, conduct auction for the grant of exploration licence for such area:`
  line
  line `Provided that upon successful completion of the auction, the Central Government shall intimate the details of`
  line `the preferred bidder in the auction to the State Government and the State Government shall grant exploration`
  line `licence for such area to such preferred bidder in such manner as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(8) The holder of exploration licence shall be entitled to a share of applicable amount quoted in the auction of`
  line `ining leases payable by the lessee to the State Government in respect of the area granted in mining lease pursuant to`
  line `the prospecting operations undertaken by the holder of such exploration licence:`
  line
  line `Provided that the share in applicable amount payable to the holder of exploration licence by the lessee of such`
  line `area shall be allowed only in respect of the minerals specified in the Seventh Schedule.`
  line
  line `(9) The Central Government shall by rules provide for the manner of conducting auction for grant of`
  line `exploration licence, including its terms and conditions, the bidding parameters for selection, share payable to the`
  line `holder of exploration licence from out of the applicable amount quoted in auction of mining leases payable by the`
  line `lessee of such area, the period for such payment and such other conditions as may be necessary.`
  line
  line `(10) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 7,---`
  line
  line `(a) the exploration licence shall be granted for a period of five years from the date of execution of the`
  line `exploration licence;`
  line
  line `(b) if, after three years from the date of execution of exploration licence, but before the date of its expiry,`
  line `the holder of the exploration licence makes an application for the extension of the period of that licence, the`
  line `State Government may, on being satisfied that within the period of five years, it shall not be possible for the`
  line `holder of such licence to complete the reconnaissance or prospecting operations for reasons beyond his control,`
  line `extend the said period to a further period not exceeding two years.`
  line
  line `(11) After three years from the date of execution of the exploration licence, the holder of such licence may`
  line `retain an area not exceeding twenty-five per cent. of the total area covered under that licence for the purpose of`
  line `continuing reconnaissance or prospecting operations and shall surrender the remaining area after submitting a`
  line `report to the State Government stating the reasons for retention of the area proposed to be retained by him and the`
  line `boundaries of that area.`
  line
  line `(12) The holder of the exploration licence shall, within three months of the completion of the operations for`
  line `which licence has been granted, or of the date of expiry of the exploration licence, whichever is earlier, submit a`
  line `geological report to the State Government explaining the result of the reconnaissance and prospecting operations,`
  line `in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(13) If the holder of the exploration licence fails to complete the reconnaissance and prospecting operations`
  line `before expiry of the exploration licence, or fails to submit the geological report within the period specified in`
  line `sub-section (12), the State Government may take such action as it deems fit, including imposition of penalty.`
  line
  line `(14) Within six months from the date of receipt of the geological report from the holder of the exploration`
  line `licence, the Central Government or the State Government shall initiate the auction process for grant of one or more`
  line `separate mining leases under section 10B or section 11 or section 11D, as the case may be, in respect of the area`
  line `where existence of mineral content is established and shall select the preferred bidder for grant of such mining`
  line `leases within one year from the date of receipt of the geological report:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case the preferred bidder is not selected within the period so specified, the State Government`
  line `shall pay to the person who was the holder of exploration licence such amount, and in such manner, as may be`
  line prescribed.]]
obj_root_law_sections_10_ba_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2015, s. 10 (w.e.f. 12-1-2015).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 16 of 2023, s. 9 (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_10_c:
  sectionId (9965)
  sectionNo 10C
  orderNo 22
  title Omitted.
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9965&sectionno=10C&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_10_c_content:
  string
  line `10C. [Grant of non-exclusive reconnaissance permits.] Omitted by the Mines and Minerals`
  line `(Development and Regulation) Amendment Act, 2021, s. 16 (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_10_c_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (9966)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 23
  title `Grant of composite licence through auction in respect of minerals other than notified minerals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9966&sectionno=11&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `^1[11. Grant of ^2[composite licence] through auction in respect of minerals other than notified`
  line `minerals.-- ^3[(1) The provisions of this section shall not apply to the,--`
  line
  line `(a) cases falling under section 17A;`
  line
  line `(b) minerals specified in Part A of the First Schedule;`
  line
  line `(c) minerals specified in Part B of the First Schedule where the grade of atomic mineral is equal to`
  line `or greater than such threshold value as maybe notified by the Central Government from time to time;`
  line or
  line
  line `(d) land in respect of which the minerals do not vest in the Government.]`
  line
  line `(2) In areas where there is evidence to show the existence of mineral contents as required by`
  line `clause (a) of sub-section (2) of section 5, the State Government shall grant a mining lease for minerals`
  line `other than notified minerals following the procedure laid down in section 10B.`
  line
  line `(3) In areas where there is inadequate evidence to show the existence of mineral contents as required`
  line `under clause (a) of sub-section (2) of section 5, the State Government shall grant a ^2[composite licence]`
  line `for minerals other than notified minerals in accordance with the procedure laid down in this section.`
  line
  line `(4) The State Government shall notify the areas in which ^2[composite licence] shall be granted for`
  line `any minerals other than notified minerals, the terms and conditions subject to which such ^2[composite`
  line `licence] shall be granted, and any other relevant conditions, in such manner as may be prescribed by the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `^4[Provided that where the State Government has not notified such area for grant of Composite licence of`
  line `any mineral (whether notified mineral or otherwise), the Central Government may require the State`
  line `Government to notify such area within a period to be fixed inconsultation with the State Government and`
  line `in cases where the notification is not issued within such period, the Central Government may notify such`
  line `area for grant of Composite licence after the expiry of the period so specified.]`
  line
  line `(5) For the purpose of granting ^2[composite licence], the State Government shall select, through`
  line `auction by method of competitive bidding, including e-auction, an applicant who fulfils the eligibility`
  line `conditions as specified in this Act.`
  line
  line `^4[Provided that--`
  line
  line `(a) where the State Government has not successfully completed auction for the purpose of`
  line `granting a composite licence in respect of any mineral (whether notified mineral or otherwise) in such notified area; or`
  line
  line `(b) upon completion of such auction, the composite licence or letter of intent for grant of composite`
  line `licence has been terminated or lapsed for any reason whatsoever,`
  line
  line `the Central Government may require the State Government to conduct and complete the auction or reauction process, as the case may be, within a period to be fixed in consultation with the State Government`
  line `and in cases where such auction or re-auction process is not completed within such period, the Central`
  line `Government may conduct auction for grant of composite licence for such area after the expiry of the`
  line `period so specified:`
  line
  line `Provided further that upon successful completion of the auction, the Central Government shall intimate`
  line `the details of the preferred bidder in the auction to the State Government and the State Government shall`
  line `grant composite licence for such area to such preferred bidder in such manner as may be prescribed by`
  line `the Central Government.]`
  line
  line `(6) The Central Government shall prescribe the terms and conditions, and procedure, subject to`
  line `which the auction shall be conducted, including the bidding parameters for the selection, which may`
  line `include a share in the production of the mineral, or any payment linked to the royalty payable, or any`
  line `other relevant parameter, or any combination or modification of them.`
  line
  line `(7) Without prejudice to the generality of sub-section (6), the Central Government shall, if it is of the`
  line `opinion that it is necessary and expedient to do so, prescribe terms and conditions, procedure and`
  line `bidding parameters in respect of categories of minerals, size and area of mineral deposits and a State or`
  line `States, subject to which the auction shall be conducted.`
  line
  line `(8) The State Government shall grant a ^2[composite licence] to an applicant selected in accordance`
  line `with the procedure laid down in this section.`
  line
  line `(9) The holder of a ^2[composite licence] shall be required to complete, within the period laid down`
  line `in section 7, the prospecting operations satisfactorily as specified in the notice inviting applications.`
  line
  line `^5[(10) On completion of the prospecting operations, the holder of the composite licence shall submit`
  line `the result of the prospecting operations in the form of a geological report to the State Government`
  line `specifying the area required for mining lease and the State Government shall grant mining lease for such`
  line `area, to the holder of the composite licence in such manner as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line Government.]]
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2015, s. 11, for section 11 (w.e.f. 12-1-2015).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 16 of 2021, s. 2, for "prospecting licence-cum-mining lease" (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 16, ibid., for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 16, ibid. (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 16 of 2021, s. 16, for sub-section (10) (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_11_a:
  sectionId (9967)
  sectionNo 11A
  orderNo 24
  title `Granting of mineral concession or composite licence in respect of coal or lignite.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9967&sectionno=11A&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_11_a_content:
  string
  line `^2[11A. Granting of ^1[mineral concession]`
  line `^3[or ^4[composite licence] in respect of coal or`
  line `lignite].--- (1) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the Central Government may, for the`
  line `purpose of granting ^1[mineral concession] ^5[or ^4[composite licence] in respect of coal or lignite] select`
  line `any of the following companies through auction by competitive bidding, on such terms and conditions as`
  line `may be prescribed, namely: ---`
  line
  line `(a) a Government company or corporation or a joint venture company formed by such company`
  line `or corporation or between the Central Government or the State Government, as the case may be, or`
  line `any other company incorporated in India; or`
  line
  line `(b) a company or a joint venture company formed by two or more companies,`
  line
  line `^6[to carry on coal or lignite reconnaissance or prospecting or mining operations, for own consumption,`
  line `sale or for any other purpose as may be determined by the Central Government;]`
  line
  line `^7[Provided that the auction by competitive bidding under this section shall not be applicable to coal`
  line `or lignite---`
  line
  line `(a) where such area is considered for allotment to a Government company or corporation or a joint`
  line `venture company formed by such company or corporation or between the Central Government or the`
  line `State Government, as the case may be, for own consumption, sale or for any other purpose as may be`
  line `determined by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) where such area is considered for allotment to a company or corporation that has been awarded`
  line `a power project on the basis of competitive bid for tariff (including Ultra Mega Power Projects);]`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, with a view to rationalise coal and lignite mines referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1), so as to ensure the coordinated and scientific development and utilisation of resources`
  line `consistent with the growing requirements of the country, from time to time, prescribe---`
  line
  line `(i) the details of mines and their location;`
  line
  line `(ii) the minimum size of such mines;`
  line
  line `(iii) such other conditions,`
  line
  line `which in the opinion of that Government may be necessary for the purpose of mining operations or`
  line `mining for sale by a company.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Government shall grant such ^8[mineral concession]`
  line `^9[or ^10[composite licence]] in respect`
  line `of any area containing coal or lignite to such company as selected through auction by ^11[competitive`
  line `bidding or through allotment] under this section:`
  line
  line `Provided that the auction by competitive bidding under this section shall not be applicable to an area`
  line `containing coal or lignite---`
  line
  line `(a) where such area is considered for allocation to a Government company or corporation or a`
  line `joint venture company formed by such company or corporation or between the Central Government`
  line `or the State Government, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(b) where such area is considered for allocation to a company or corporation or that has been`
  line `awarded a power project on the basis of competitive bids for tariff (including Ultra Mega Power`
  line `Projects).`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of this section, "company" means a company as defined in`
  line `clause (20) of section 2 of the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013).]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 16 of 2021, s. 2, "reconnaissance permit, prospecting licence or mining lease" (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 11 of 2015, s. 28 and the Fourth Schedule, for section 11A (w.e.f. 21-10-2014).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 2 of 2020, s. 7 (w.e.f. 10-1-2020).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 16 of 2021, s. 2, for "prospecting licence-cum-mining lease" (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 2 of 2020, s. 7, for "in respect of any area containing coal or lignite" (w.e.f. 10-1-2020).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 2 of 2020, s. 7, for the long line (w.e.f. 10-1-2020).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-1-2020).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 16 of 2021, s. 2, "reconnaissance permit, prospecting licence or mining lease" (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line
  line `9. Ins. by Act 2 of 2020, s. 7 (w.e.f. 10-1-2020).`
  line
  line `10.Subs. by Act 16 of 2021, s. 2, for "prospecting licence-cum-mining lease" (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line
  line `11. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for "competitive bidding or otherwise" (w.e.f. 10-1-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_11_b:
  sectionId (9968)
  sectionNo 11B
  orderNo 25
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules for regulating atomic minerals specified under Part B of First Schedule.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9968&sectionno=11B&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_11_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[11B. Power of Central Government to make rules for regulating atomic minerals specified`
  line `under Part B of First Schedule.--The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for regulating the grant of mining leases or other mineral concessions in respect of minerals`
  line `specified in Part B of the First Schedule and for purposes connected therewith, and the State Government`
  line `shall grant a ^2[mineral concession] in respect of any such mineral in accordance with such rules.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2015, s. 12 (w.e.f. 12-1-2015).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 16 of 2021, s. 2, "reconnaissance permit, prospecting licence or mining lease" (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_11_c:
  sectionId (9969)
  sectionNo 11C
  orderNo 26
  title `Power of Central Government to amend First Schedule and Fourth Schedule.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2015, s. 12 (w.e.f. 12-1-2015).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9969&sectionno=11C&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_11_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[11C. Power of Central Government to amend First Schedule and Fourth Schedule.--The`
  line `Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, amend the First Schedule and the`
  line `Fourth Schedule so as to add or delete any mineral as may be specified in the notification.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_d:
  sectionId (77315)
  sectionNo 11D
  orderNo 27
  title `Central Government to conduct auction for grant of mining lease or composite licence in respect of minerals specified in Part D of First Schedule.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 16 of 2023, s. 10 (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=77315&sectionno=11D&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_11_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[11D.Central Government to conduct auction for grant of mining lease or composite licence in respect`
  line `of minerals specified in Part D of First Schedule.--(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the`
  line `Central Government shall, for the purpose of granting mining lease or composite licence in any area in respect of`
  line `any mineral specified in the Part D of the First Schedule, select, through auction by method of competitive bidding,`
  line `including e-auction, a preferred bidder who fulfils the eligibility conditions as specified in section 5, on such terms`
  line `and conditions, and in such manner, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Upon successful completion of the auction, the Central Government shall intimate the details of the`
  line `preferred bidder in the auction to the State Government and the State Government shall grant mining lease or`
  line `composite licence for such area, to such preferred bidder, in such manner, as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(3) The royalty, dead rent, applicable amount quoted in the auction and any other statutory`
  line `payment in relation to the mining lease or composite licence auctioned by the Central Government`
  line `shall accrue to the State Government or concerned authorities, as the case may be, as if the auction`
  line `has been conducted by the State Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (9970)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 28
  title `Registers of prospecting licences and mining leases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9970&sectionno=12&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `12. ^1[Registers of mineral concession.]--- (1) The State Government shall cause to be maintained in the`
  line `prescribed form---`
  line
  line `(a) a register of applications for prospecting licences;`
  line
  line `(b) a register of prospecting licensees;`
  line
  line `^2[(c) a register of applications for mining leases;`
  line
  line `(d) a register of mining lessees;`
  line
  line `(e) a register of applications for reconnaissance permits; ^3***`
  line
  line `(f) a register of reconnaissance permits,]`
  line
  line `^4[(g) a register of applications for exploration licences; and`
  line
  line `(h) a register of exploration licence,]`
  line
  line `in each of which shall be entered such particulars as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such register shall be open to inspection by any person on payment of such fee as the State`
  line `Government may fix.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 16 of 2023, s. 11 for the marginal heading (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 38 of 1999, s. 13, for clauses (c) and (d) (w.e.f. 18-12-1999).`
  line
  line `3. The word "and" omitted by Act 16 of 2023, s. 11 (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 16 of 2023, s. 11 (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_12_a:
  sectionId (9971)
  sectionNo 12A
  orderNo 29
  title `Transfer of mineral concessions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9971&sectionno=12A&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[12A. Transfer of mineral concessions.--- (1) The provisions of this section shall not apply to`
  line `minerals specified in Part A or Part B of the First Schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) A holder of a mining lease or a ^2[composite licence ^3 [or exploration licence]] granted in accordance with the procedure`
  line `laid down in ^4[this Act] may, with the previous approval of the State Government, transfer his mining`
  line `lease or ^2[composite licence ^3[or exploration licence]], as the case may be, in such manner as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line `Government, to any person eligible to hold such mining lease or ^2[composite licence^3[or exploration licence]] in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder.`
  line
  line `^5[Provided that the transferee of mining lease shall not be required to pay the amount or transfer`
  line `charges referred to in sub-section (6), as it stood prior to the commencement of the Mines and Minerals`
  line `(Development and Regulation) Amendment Act, 2021, after such commencement but no refund shall be`
  line `made of the charges already paid.]`
  line
  line `(3) If the State Government does not convey its previous approval for transfer of such mining lease`
  line `or ^2[composite licence ^3[or exploration licence]], as the case may be, within a period of ninety days from the date of receiving`
  line `such notice, it shall be construed that the State Government has no objection to such transfer:`
  line
  line `Provided that the holder of the original mining lease or ^2[composite licence ^3[or exploration licence]] shall intimate to the`
  line `State Government the consideration payable by the successor-in-interest for the transfer, including the`
  line `consideration in respect of the prospecting operations already undertaken and the reports and data`
  line `generated during the operations.`
  line
  line `(4) No such transfer of a mining lease or ^2[composite licence ^3[or exploration licence]], referred to in`
  line `sub-section (2), shall take place if the State Government, within the notice period and for reasons to be communicated in writing, disapproves the transfer on the ground that the transferee is not eligible as per`
  line `the provisions of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such transfer of a mining lease ^6[or composite licence], shall be made in`
  line `contravention of any condition subject to which the mining lease or the ^2[composite licence ^3[or exploration licence]] was granted.`
  line
  line `(5) All transfers effected under this section shall be subject to the condition that the transferee has`
  line `accepted all the conditions and liabilities under any law for the time being in force which the transferor`
  line `was subject to in respect of such a mining lease or ^2[composite licence ^3[or exploration licence]], as the case may be.`
  line
  line `^7* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_12_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2015, s. 13 (w.e.f. 12-1-2015).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 16 of 2021, s. 2, for "prospecting licence-cum-mining lease" (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 16 of 2023, s. 12 (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 17, ibid., for "section 10B or section 11" (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 16 of 2021, s. 17, (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 16 of 2023, s. 12, for "or of a composite licence" (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `7. Sub-section (6) omitted by Act 16 of 2021, s. 17, (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (9972)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 30
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules in respect of minerals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9972&sectionno=13&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `^1[RULES FOR REGULATING THE GRANT OF MINERAL CONCESSIONS]`
  line
  line `13. Power of Central Government to make rules in respect of minerals.--- (1) The Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make rules for regulating the grant of ^2[mineral`
  line `concession] in respect of minerals and for purposes connected therewith.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the person by whom, and the manner in which, applications for ^2[mineral concession] in`
  line `respect of land in which the minerals vest in the Government may be made and the fees to be paid`
  line therefor;
  line
  line `^3[(aa) the conditions as may be necessary for commencement and continuation of production by`
  line `the holders of mining leases, under section 4B;`
  line
  line `(ab) the conditions to be fulfilled by the new lessee for obtaining all necessary rights, approvals,`
  line `clearances, licences and the like under the proviso to sub-section (2) of section 8B;`
  line
  line `^4* * * * *]`
  line
  line `(b) the time within which, and the form in which, acknowledgement of the receipt of any such`
  line `application may be sent;`
  line
  line `(c) the matters which may be considered where applications in respect of the same land are`
  line `received on the same day;`
  line
  line `^5[(d) the terms, conditions and process of auction by competitive bidding and allotment in`
  line `respect of coal or lignite;`
  line
  line `(da) the regulation of grant of ^6[mineral concession] or ^7[composite licence] in respect of coal or`
  line lignite;
  line
  line `(db) the details of mines and their location, the minimum size of such mines and such other`
  line `conditions which may be necessary for the purpose of coal or lignite reconnaissance, prospecting or`
  line `mining operations;`
  line
  line `(dc) utilisation of coal or lignite including mining for sale by a company;]`
  line
  line `(e) the authority by which ^6[mineral concession] in respect of land in which the minerals vest in`
  line `the Government may be granted;`
  line
  line `(f) the procedure for obtaining ^8[a ^6[mineral concession]] in respect of any land in which the`
  line `minerals vest in a person other than the Government and the terms on which, and the conditions`
  line `subject to which, such ^9[a permit, licence or lease] may be granted or renewed;`
  line
  line `(g) the terms on which, and the conditions subject to which, any other ^6[mineral concession] may`
  line `be granted or renewed;`
  line
  line `(h) the facilities to be afforded by holders of mining leases to persons deputed by the`
  line `Government for the purpose of undertaking research or training in matters relating to mining`
  line operations;
  line
  line `^10[(i) the fixing and collection of fees for ^6[mineral concession], surface rent, security deposit,`
  line `fines, other fees or charges and the time within which and the manner in which the dead rent or`
  line `royalty shall be payable;]`
  line
  line `(j) the manner in which rights of third parties may be protected (whether by payment of`
  line `compensation or otherwise) in cases where any such party may be prejudicially affected by reason of`
  line `any ^11[reconnaissance, prospecting or mining operations];`
  line
  line `^12[(jj) parameters of existence of mineral contents under clause (a) of sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 5;]`
  line
  line `(k) the grouping of associated minerals for the purposes of section 6;`
  line
  line `^13[(ka) terms and conditions and additional amount under sub-section (2) of section 6A;]`
  line
  line `(l) the manner in which, and the conditions subject to which, ^8[a ^6[mineral concession]] may be`
  line transferred;
  line
  line `(m) the construction, maintenance and use of roads, power transmission lines, tramways,`
  line `railways, aerial ropeways, pipelines and the making of passages for water for mining purposes on`
  line `any land comprised in a mining lease;`
  line
  line `(n) the form of registers to be maintained under this Act;`
  line
  line `^14* * * * *`
  line
  line `(p) the reports and statements to be submitted by holders of ^15[mineral concession] or owners of`
  line `mines and the authority to which such reports and statements shall be submitted;`
  line
  line `(q) the period within which applications for revision of any order passed by a State Government`
  line `or other authority in exercise of any power conferred by or under this Act, may be made ^16[the fees to`
  line `be paid therefore and the documents which shall accompany such applications] and the manner in`
  line `which such applications shall be disposed of; ^17***`
  line
  line `^16[(qq) the manner in which rehabilitation of flora and other vegetation such as trees, shrubs and`
  line `the like destroyed by reason of any prospecting or mining operations shall be made in the same area`
  line `or in any other area selected by the Central Government (whether by way of reimbursement of the`
  line `cost of rehabilitation or otherwise) by the person holding the prospecting licence or mining lease;]`
  line
  line `^18[(qqa) the amount of payment to be made to the District Mineral Foundation under`
  line `sub-sections (5) and (6) of section 9B;`
  line
  line `(qqb) the manner of usage of funds accrued to the ^19[National Mineral Exploration and`
  line `Development Trust] under sub-section (2) of section 9C;`
  line
  line `(qqc) the composition and functions of the ^19[National Mineral Exploration and Development`
  line `Trust] under sub-section (3) of section 9C;`
  line
  line `(qqd) the manner of payment of amount to the ^19[National Mineral Exploration and Development`
  line `Trust] under sub-section (4) of section 9C;`
  line
  line `(qqe) the terms and conditions subject to which mining leases shall be granted under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 10B;`
  line
  line `(qqf) the terms and conditions, and procedure, subject to which the auction shall be conducted`
  line `including the bidding parameters for the selection under sub-section (5) of section 10B;`
  line
  line `(qqg) the time limits for various stages in processing applications for grant of ^20[mineral`
  line `concession under section 10B, 10BA, 11, 11A, 11B, 11D], and section 17A, and their renewals;`
  line
  line `^21* * * * *`
  line
  line `(qqi) the terms and conditions for grant of ^7[composite licence] under`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(qqj) the terms and conditions, and procedure, including the bidding parameters for the selection`
  line `under sub-section (6) of section 11;`
  line
  line `^22[(qqja) the terms and conditions and amount or transfer charges under the proviso to`
  line `sub-section (6) of section 12A;]`
  line
  line `^23* * * * *`
  line
  line `^24[(r) the period of mining lease under sub-section (4) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(s) the manner of sale of mineral by the holder of a mining lease under sub-section (5) of`
  line `section 8;`
  line
  line `(t) the manner of sale of mineral under-sub-section (7A) of section 8A;`
  line
  line `(u) the manner for reimbursement of expenditure towards reconnaissance permits or prospecting`
  line `operations under the second proviso to clause (b) of sub-section (2) of section 10A;`
  line
  line `(v) the manner of granting mining lease to the preferred bidder under the second proviso to`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 10B;`
  line
  line `^25[(va) the manner of notifying the areas for grant of exploration licence under sub-section (4) of`
  line `section 10BA;`
  line
  line `(vb) the manner of granting exploration licence to the preferred bidder under the proviso to`
  line `sub-section (7) of section 10BA;`
  line
  line `(vc) the manner of conducting auction for grant of exploration licence, the terms and conditions`
  line `thereof, the bidding parameters for selection, the share payable to the holder, the period for payment`
  line `and other conditions under sub-section (9) of section 10BA;`
  line
  line `(vd) the manner of submitting geological report under sub-section (12) of section 10BA;`
  line
  line `(ve) the amount to be paid and the manner of payment under the proviso to sub-section (14) of`
  line `section 10BA;]`
  line
  line `(w) the manner of granting composite licence to the preferred bidder under the second proviso to`
  line `sub-section (5) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(x) the manner of granting mining lease by the State Government to the holder of the composite`
  line `licence under sub-section (10) of section 11;`
  line
  line `^25[(xa) the terms and conditions and the manner of selecting a preferred bidder under sub-section`
  line `(1) of section 11D;`
  line
  line `(xb) the manner of granting a mining lease or composite licence to a preferred bidder under subsection (2) of section 11D;]`
  line
  line `^13[(xc) conditions for inclusion of any mineral other than minor mineral in a lease granted in`
  line `respect of a minor mineral under sub-section (5) of section 15B;]`
  line
  line `(y) any other matter which is to be, or may be prescribed, under this Act.]`
