  line `24. Subs. by s. 18, ibid., for cl. (r) (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line
  line `25. Ins. by Act 16 of 2023, s. 14 (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_13_a:
  sectionId (9973)
  sectionNo 13A
  orderNo 31
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules for grant of prospecting licences or mining leases in respect of territorial waters or continental shelf of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 56 of 1972, s. 6 (w.e.f. 12-9-1972).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9973&sectionno=13A&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_13_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[13A. Power of Central Government to make rules for the grant of prospecting licences or`
  line `mining leases in respect of territorial waters or continental shelf of India.--- (1) The Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make rules for the grant of prospecting licences`
  line `or mining leases in respect of any minerals underlying the ocean within the territorial waters or the`
  line `continental shelf of India.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may provide for all or any`
  line `of the following matters, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the conditions, limitations and restrictions subject to which such prospecting licences or`
  line `mining leases may be granted;`
  line
  line `(b) regulation of exploration and exploitation of minerals within the territorial waters or the`
  line `continental shelf of India;`
  line
  line `(c) ensuring that such exploration or exploitation does not interfere with navigation and`
  line
  line `(d) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (9974)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 32
  title `[Sections 5 to 13] not to apply to minor minerals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9974&sectionno=14&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `14. ^1[Sections 5 to 13] not to apply to minor minerals.---The provisions of ^1[sections 5 to 13]`
  line `(inclusive) shall not apply to ^2[quarry leases, mining leases or other mineral concessions] in respect of`
  line `minor minerals.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 37 of 1986, s. 12, for "sections 4 to 13" (w.e.f. 10-2-1987).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 56 of 1972, s. 7, for "prospecting licences and mining leases" (w.e.f. 12-9-1972).`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (9975)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 33
  title `Power of State Governments to make rules in respect of minor minerals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9975&sectionno=15&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make rules for, regulating the grant of ^1[quarry`
  line `leases, mining leases or other mineral concessions] in respect of minor minerals and for purposes`
  line `connected therewith.`
  line
  line `^2[(1A) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the person by whom and the manner in which, applications for quarry leases, mining leases`
  line `or other mineral concessions may be made and the fees to be paid therefor;`
  line
  line `(b) the time within which, and the form in which, acknowledgement of the receipt of any such`
  line `applications may be sent;`
  line
  line `(c) the matters which may be considered where applications in respect of the same land are`
  line `received within the same day;`
  line
  line `(d) the terms on which, and the conditions subject to which and the authority by which quarry`
  line `leases, mining leases or other mineral concessions may be granted or renewed;`
  line
  line `(e) the procedure for obtaining quarry leases, mining leases or other mineral concessions;`
  line
  line `(f) the facilities to be afforded by holders of quarry leases, mining leases or other mineral`
  line `concessions to persons deputed by the Government for the purpose of undertaking research or`
  line `training in matters relating to mining operations;`
  line
  line `(g) the fixing and collection of rent, royalty, fees, dead rent, fines or other charges and the time`
  line `within which and the manner in which these shall be payable;`
  line
  line `(h) the manner in which rights of third parties may be protected (whether by way of payment of`
  line `compensation or otherwise) in cases where any such party is prejudicially affected by reason of any`
  line `prospecting or mining operations;`
  line
  line `(i) the manner in which rehabilitation of flora and other vegetation such as trees, shrubs and the`
  line `like destroyed by reason of any quarrying or mining operations shall be made in the same area or in`
  line `any other area selected by the State Government (whether by way of reimbursement of the cost of`
  line `rehabilitation or otherwise) by the person holding the quarrying or mining lease;`
  line
  line `(j) the manner in which and the conditions subject to which, a quarry lease, mining lease or other`
  line `mineral concession may be transferred;`
  line
  line `(k) the construction, maintenance and use of roads power transmission lines, tramways, railways,`
  line `serial rope ways, pipelines and the making of passage for water for mining purposes on any land`
  line `comprised in a quarry or mining lease or other mineral concession;`
  line
  line `(l) the form of registers to be maintained under this Act;`
  line
  line `(m) the reports and statements to be submitted by holders of quarry or mining leases or other`
  line `mineral concessions and the authority to which such reports and statements shall be submitted;`
  line
  line `(n) the period within which and the manner in which and the authority to which applications for`
  line `revision of any order passed by any authority under these rules may be made, the fees to be paid`
  line `therefore, and the powers of the revisional authority; and`
  line
  line `(o) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed.]`
  line
  line `(2) Until rules are made under sub-section (1), any rules made by a state Government regulating the`
  line `grant of ^3[quarry leases, mining leases or other mineral concessions] in respect of minor minerals which`
  line `are in force immediately before the commencement of these Act shall continue in force.`
  line
  line `^4[(3) The holder of a mining lease or any other mineral concession granted under any rule made`
  line `under sub-section (1) shall pay ^5[royalty or dead rent, whichever is more] in respect of minor minerals`
  line `removed or consumed by him or by his agent, manager, employee, contractor or sub-lessee at the rate`
  line `prescribed for the time being in the rules framed by the State Government in respect of minor minerals:`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Government shall not enhance the rate of ^6[royalty or dead rent] in respect of`
  line `any minor mineral for more than once during any period of ^7[three] years.]`
  line
  line `^8[(4) Without prejudice to sub-sections (1), (2) and sub-section (3), the State Government may, by`
  line `notification, make rules for regulating the provisions of this Act for the following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner in which the District Mineral Foundation shall work for the interest and benefit`
  line `of persons and areas affected by mining under sub-section (2) of section 9B;`
  line
  line `(b) the composition and functions of the District Mineral Foundation under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 9B; and`
  line
  line `(c) the amount of payment to be made to the District Mineral Foundation by concession holders`
  line `of minor minerals under section 15A.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 56 of 1972, s. 8, for "prospecting licence and mining leases" (w.e.f. 12-9-1972).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 37 of 1986, s. 13 (w.e.f. 10-2-1987).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 56 of 1972, s. 8, for "prospecting licence and mining leases" (w.e.f. 12-9-1972).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 12-9-1972).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 37 of 1986, s. 13, for "royalty" (w.e.f. 10-2-1987).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 37 of 1986, s. 13, for "royalty" (w.e.f. 10-2-1987).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by s. 13, ibid., for "four" (w.e.f. 10-2-1987).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by Act 10 of 2015, s. 15 (w.e.f. 12-1-2015).`
obj_root_law_sections_15_a:
  sectionId (9976)
  sectionNo 15A
  orderNo 34
  title `Power of State Government to collect funds for District Mineral Foundation in case of minor minerals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2015, s. 16, (w.e.f. 12-1-2015).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9976&sectionno=15A&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[15A. Power of State Government to collect funds for District Mineral Foundation in case of`
  line `minor minerals.--- The State Government may prescribe the payment by all holders of concessions`
  line `related to minor minerals of amounts to the District Mineral Foundation of the district in which the`
  line `mining operations are carried on.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_b:
  sectionId (100319)
  sectionNo 15B
  orderNo 35
  title `Inclusion of other minerals in mining lease.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 28 of 2025, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-9-2025).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=100319&sectionno=15B&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_15_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[15B. Inclusion of other minerals in mining lease.--- (1) A holder of a mining lease may apply to`
  line `the State Government for inclusion of any other mineral in his mining lease on the basis of a geological`
  line `report in relation to that lease and the State Government shall permit inclusion of such mineral within`
  line `sixty days of such application, subject to the payment of such additional amount on dispatch of the`
  line `included mineral as specified in the Eighth Schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, and for reasons to be`
  line `recorded in writing, amend the Eighth Schedule so as to modify the entries mentioned therein with effect`
  line `from such date as may be specified in the said notification.`
  line
  line `(3) The holder of mining lease shall submit such reports or returns to the State Government and any`
  line `other authority in respect of the included mineral as may be specified by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) The provision of this section shall apply for inclusion of any minor mineral in a lease granted in`
  line `respect of a mineral other than minor mineral and the State Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, specify the royalty and other payments to be made by the lessee on dispatch of such`
  line `included minor mineral.`
  line
  line `(5) Inclusion of any mineral other than minor mineral in a lease granted in respect of a minor mineral`
  line `shall be made in accordance with the conditions as may be prescribed for this purpose by the Central`
  line `Government and such rules may provide for all or any of the matters, namely:---`
  line
  line `(i) the extent of presence of mineral other than minor mineral as compared to minor mineral in the`
  line lease;
  line
  line `(ii) termination of the lease in the interest of regulation of mines and mineral development and`
  line `grant of a fresh lease in the area as a lease in respect of mineral other than minor mineral;`
  line
  line `(iii) regulation of such lease as a lease granted for mineral other than minor minerals;`
  line
  line `(iv) additional payment as specified in the Eighth Schedule to be made upon inclusion of a mineral`
  line `other than minor mineral.`
  line
  line `(6) Any mineral may be included under this section in a mining lease granted in respect of atomic`
  line `mineral specified in Part B of the First Schedule where the grade of atomic mineral is equal to or above`
  line `the notified threshold value with prior approval of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(7) No atomic mineral as specified in Part B of the First Schedule where the grade of atomic mineral`
  line `is equal to or above the notified threshold value shall be included in the mining lease granted in respect`
  line `of minerals other than such atomic minerals.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (9977)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 36
  title `Power to modify mining leases granted before 25th October, 1949.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9977&sectionno=16&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) (a) All mining`
  line `leases granted before the commencement of the Mines and Minerals (Regulation and Development)`
  line `Amendment Act, 1972 (56 of 1972) ^2[if in force at the date of commencement of the Mines and Minerals`
  line `(Regulation and Development) Amendment Act, 1994 (25 of 1994), shall be brought in conformity with`
  line `the provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder within two years from the date of the`
  line `commencement of the Mines and Minerals (Regulation and Development) Amendment Act, 1994], or`
  line `such further time as the Central Government may, by general or special order, specify in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(b) Where the rights under any mining lease, granted by the proprietor of an estate or tenure before`
  line `the commencement of the Mines and Minerals (Regulation and Development) Amendment Act, 1972`
  line `(56 of 1972), have vested, on or after the 25th day of October, 1949, in the State Government in`
  line `pursuance of the provisions of any Act of any Provincial or State Legislature which provides for the`
  line `acquisition of estates or tenures or provides for agrarian reform, such mining lease shall be brought into`
  line `conformity with the provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder within ^3[two years from the`
  line `commencement of the Mines and Minerals (Regulation and Development) Amendment Act, 1994 (25 of`
  line `1994)], or within such further time as the Central Government may, by general or special order, specify`
  line `in this behalf.]`
  line
  line `^4[(1A) Where any action is taken under clause (a) or clause (b) of sub-section (1) to bring the period`
  line `of any lease in conformity with the provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder, then`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in section 8, the period of such lease shall continue to operate for a`
  line `period of two years from the date of bringing such lease in conformity with the provisions of this Act.]`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make rules for the purpose`
  line `of giving effect to the provisions of sub-section (1) and in particular such rules shall provide--`
  line
  line `(a) for giving previous notice of the modification or alteration proposed to be made in any`
  line `existing mining lease to the lessee and where the lessor is not the Central Government, also to the`
  line `lessor and for affording him an opportunity of showing cause against the proposal;`
  line
  line `(b) for the payment of compensation to the lessee in respect of the reduction of any area covered`
  line `by the existing mining lease; and`
  line
  line `(c) for the principles on which, the manner in which, and the authority by which, the said`
  line `compensation shall be determined.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 56 of 1972, s. 9, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 12-9-1972).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 1994, s. 6, for certain words (w.e.f. 25-1-1994).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 25-1-1994).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 25-1-1994).`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (9978)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 37
  title `Special powers of Central Government to undertake prospecting or mining operations in certain lands.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9978&sectionno=17&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of this section shall apply ^1*** in respect of land in which the`
  line `minerals vest in the Government of a State ^2[or any other person].`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the Central Government, after consultation with`
  line `the State Government, may undertakes`
  line `^3[mineral concession] in any area not already held under any`
  line `^3[mineral concession] and where it proposes to do so, it shall, by notification in the Official Gazette--`
  line
  line `(a) specify the boundaries of such area;`
  line
  line `(b) state whether ^4[reconnaissance, prospecting or mining operations] will be carried out in the`
  line `area; and`
  line
  line `(c) specify the mineral or minerals in respect of which such operations will be carried out.`
  line
  line `(3) Where, in exercise of the powers conferred by sub-section (2), the Central Government`
  line `undertakes ^4[reconnaissance, prospecting or mining operations] in any area, the Central Government`
  line `shall be liable to pay ^5[reconnaissance permit fee or prospecting fee] royalty, surface rent or dead rent, as`
  line `the case may be, at the same rate at which it would have been payable under this Act, if such`
  line `^4[reconnaissance, prospecting or mining operations] had been undertaken by a private person under a`
  line `^3[mineral concession].`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government, with a view to enabling it to exercise the powers conferred on it by`
  line `sub-section (2) may, after consultation with the State Government, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, declare that no ^3[mineral concession] shall be granted in respect of any land specified in the`
  line notification.
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The word "only" omitted by Act 56 of 1972, s. 10 (w.e.f. 12-9-1972).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 10, ibid. (w.e.f. 12-9-1972).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 16 of 2021, s. 2, "reconnaissance permit, prospecting licence or mining lease" (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 38 of 1999, s. 15, for "prospecting or mining operations" (w.e.f. 18-12-1999).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 15, ibid., for "prospecting fee" (w.e.f. 18-12-1999).`
obj_root_law_sections_17_a:
  sectionId (9979)
  sectionNo 17A
  orderNo 38
  title `Reservation of areas for purposes of conservation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9979&sectionno=17A&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_17_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[17A. Reservation of areas for purposes of conservation.--- (1) The Central Government, with a`
  line `view to conserving any mineral and after consultation with the State Government, may reserve any area`
  line `not already held under any prospecting licence ^2[or exploration licence] or mining lease and, where it`
  line `proposes to do so, it shall, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify the boundaries of such area and`
  line `the mineral or minerals in respect of which such area will be reserved.`
  line
  line `^3[(1A) The Central Government may in consultation with the State Government, reserve any area not`
  line `already held under any prospecting licence ^2[or exploration licence] or mining lease, for undertaking`
  line `prospecting or mining operations through a Government company or corporation owned or controlled by`
  line `it, and where it proposes to do so, it shall, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify the boundaries`
  line `of such area and the mineral or minerals in respect of which such area will be reserved.]`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may, with the approval of the Central Government, reserve any area not`
  line `already held under any prospecting licence ^2[or exploration licence] or mining lease, for undertaking`
  line `prospecting or mining operations through a Government company or corporation owned or controlled by`
  line `it ^4*** and where it proposes to do so, it shall, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify the`
  line `boundaries of such area and the mineral or minerals in respect of which such areas will be reserved.`
  line
  line `^5[^6[(2A) Where in exercise of the powers conferred by sub-section (1A) or sub-section (2), the`
  line `Central Government or the State Government, as the case may be, reserves any area for undertaking`
  line `prospecting or mining operations or prospecting operations followed by mining operations, the State`
  line `Government shall grant prospecting licence, mining lease or composite licence, as the case may be, in`
  line `respect of such area to such Government company or corporation within the period specified in this`
  line `section:`
  line
  line `Provided that in respect of any mineral specified in Part B of the First Schedule, the State`
  line `Government shall grant the prospecting licence, mining lease or composite licence, as the case may be,`
  line `only after obtaining the previous approval of the Central Government.]`
  line
  line `(2B) Where the Government company or corporation is desirous of carrying out the prospecting`
  line `operations or mining operations in a joint venture with other persons, the joint venture partner shall be`
  line `selected through a competitive process, and such Government company or corporation shall hold more`
  line `than seventy-four per cent. of the paid up share capital in such joint venture.`
  line
  line `(2C) A mining lease granted to a Government company or corporation, or a joint venture, referred to`
  line `in sub-sections (2A) and (2B), shall be granted on payment of such amount as ^7[specified in the Fifth`
  line `Schedule:].]`
  line
  line `^8[Provided that the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette and for reasons to`
  line `be recorded in writing, amend the Fifth Schedule so as to modify the entries mentioned therein in the said`
  line `Schedule with effect from such date as may be specified in the said notification.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that all such Government companies or`
  line `corporations whose mining lease has been granted after the commencement of the Mines and Minerals`
  line `(Development and Regulation) Amendment Act, 2015 (10 of 2015), shall also pay such additional amount`
  line `as specified in the Fifth Schedule for the mineral produced after the commencement of the Mines and`
  line `Minerals (Development and Regulation)Amendment Act, 2021 (16 of 2021).]`
  line
  line `(3)^9[Where in exercise of the powers conferred by sub-section (1A) or sub-section (2) the Central`
  line `Government or the State Government, as the case may be,] undertakes prospecting or mining operations`
  line `in any area in which the minerals vest in a private person, it shall be liable to pay prospecting fee,`
  line `royalty, surface rent or dead rent, as the case may be, from time to time at the same rate at which it`
  line `would have been payable under this Act if such prospecting or mining operations had been undertaken`
  line `by a private person under prospecting licence or mining lease.]`
  line
  line `^10[(4) The reservation made under this section shall lapse in case no mining lease is granted within a`
  line `period of five years from the date of such reservation:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the period of five years from the date of reservation has expired before the date`
  line `of commencement of the Mines and Minerals (Development and Regulation) Amendment Act, 2021`
  line `(16 of 2021) or expires within a period of one year from the date of commencement of the said Act, the`
  line `reservation shall lapse in case no mining lease is granted within a period of one year from the date of`
  line `commencement of the said Act:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the State Government may, on an application made by such Government`
  line `company or corporation or on its own motion, and on being satisfied that it shall not be possible to grant`
  line `the mining lease within the said period, make an order with reasons in writing, within a period of three months from the date of receipt of such application, to relax such period by a further period not`
  line `exceeding one year:`
  line
  line `Provided also that where the Government company or corporation in whose favour an area has been`
  line `reserved under this section before the commencement of the Mines and Minerals (Development and`
  line `Regulation) Amendment Act, 2015 (10 of 2015), has commenced production from the reserved area`
  line `without execution of mining lease, such Government company or corporation shall be deemed to have`
  line `become lessee of the State Government from the date of commencement of mining operations and such`
  line `deemed lease shall lapse upon execution of the mining lease in accordance with this sub-section or expiry`
  line `of period of one year from the date of commencement of the Mines and Minerals (Development and`
  line `Regulation)Amendment Act, 2021 (16 of 2021), whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line `(5) The termination or lapse of mining lease shall result in the lapse of the reservation under this`
  line section.]
obj_root_law_sections_17_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 37 of 1986, s. 14 (w.e.f. 10-2-1987).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 16 of 2023, s. 15 (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 25 of 1994, s. 7 (w.e.f. 25-1-1994).`
  line
  line `4. The words "or by the Central Government" omitted by Act 25 of 1994, s. 7 (w.e.f. 25-1-1994).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 10 of 2015, s. 17 (w.e.f. 12-1-2015).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 16 of 2021, s. 19, for sub-section (2A) (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by s. 19, ibid., for "may be prescribed by the Central Government" (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by s. 19, ibid. (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by Act 25 of 1994, s. 7, for "Where in exercise of the powers conferred by sub-section (2) the State Government"`
  line `(w.e.f. 25-1-1994).`
  line
  line `10. Ins. by Act 16 of 2021, s. 19 (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (9980)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 39
  title `Mineral Development.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9980&sectionno=18&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the duty of the Central Government to take all such steps`
  line `as may be necessary ^1[for the conservation and systematic development of minerals in India and for the`
  line `protection of environment by preventing or controlling any pollution which may be caused by`
  line `prospecting or mining operations] and ^2[for such purposes] the Central Government may, by notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette, make such rules as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the opening of new mines and the regulation of mining operations in any area;`
  line
  line `(b) the regulation of the excavation or collection of minerals from any mine;`
  line
  line `(c) the measures to be taken by owners of mines for the purpose of beneficiation of ores,`
  line `including the provision of suitable contrivances for such purpose;`
  line
  line `(d) the development of mineral resources in any area;`
  line
  line `(e) the notification of all new borings and shaft sinkings and the preservation of bore-hole`
  line `records, and specimens of cores of alt new bore-holes;`
  line
  line `(f) the regulation of the arrangements for the storage of minerals and the stocks thereof that may`
  line `be kept by any person;`
  line
  line `(g) the submission of samples of minerals from any mine by the owner thereof and the manner in`
  line `which and the authority to which such samples shall be submitted; and the taking of samples of any`
  line `minerals from any mine by the State Government or any other authority specified by it in that behalf;`
  line
  line `(h) the submission by owners of mines of such special or periodical returns and reports as may`
  line `be specified, and the form in which and the authority to which such returns and reports shall be`
  line submitted;
  line
  line `^3[(i) the regulation of prospecting operations;`
  line
  line `(j) the employment of qualified geologists or mining engineers to supervise prospecting or`
  line `mining operations;`
  line
  line `(k) the disposal or discharge of waste slime or tailings arising from any mining or metallurgical`
  line `operations carried out in a mine;`
  line
  line `(l) the manner in which and the authority by which directions may be issued to the owners of`
  line `any mine to do or refrain from doing certain things in the interest of conservation or systematic`
  line `development of minerals or for the protection of environment by preventing or controlling pollution`
  line `which may be caused by prospecting or mining operations;`
  line
  line `(m) the maintenance and submission of such plans, registers or records as may be specified by`
  line `the Government;`
  line
  line `(n) the submission of records or reports by persons carrying on prospecting or mining operations`
  line `regarding any research in mining or geology carried out by them;`
  line
  line `(o) the facilities to be afforded by persons carrying out prospecting or mining operations to`
  line `persons authorised by the Central Government for the purpose of undertaking research or training in`
  line `matters relating to mining or geology;`
  line
  line `(p) the procedure for and the manner of imposition of fines for the contravention of any of the`
  line `rules framed under this section and the authority who may impose such fines; and`
  line
  line `(q) the authority to which, the period within which, the form and the manner in which`
  line `applications for revision of any order passed by any authority under this Act and the rules made`
  line `thereunder may be made, the fee to be paid and the documents which should accompany such`
  line applications.]
  line
  line `(3) All rules made under this section shall be binding on the Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 37 of 1986, s. 15, for "for the conservation and development of minerals in India" (w.e.f. 10-2-1987).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 15, ibid., for "for that purpose" (w.e.f. 10-2-1987).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 15, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-2-1987).`
obj_root_law_sections_18_a:
  sectionId (9981)
  sectionNo 18A
  orderNo 40
  title `Power to authorise Geological Survey of India, etc., to make investigation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9981&sectionno=18A&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_18_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[18A. Power to authorise Geological Survey of India, etc., to make investigation.--- (1) Where`
  line `the Central Government is of opinion that for the conservation and development of minerals in India, it`
  line `is necessary to collect as precise information as possible with regard to any mineral available in or under`
  line `any land in relation to which any prospecting licence ^2[or exploration licence] or mining lease has been`
  line `granted, whether by the State Government or by any other person, the Central Government may`
  line `authorise the Geological Survey of India, or such other authority or agency as it may specify in this`
  line `behalf, to carry out such detailed investigations for the purpose of obtaining such information as may be`
  line `necessary:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the cases of prospecting licences ^2[or exploration licence] or mining leases granted`
  line `by a State Government, no such authorisation shall be made except after consultation with the State`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(2) On the issue of any authorisation under sub-section (1), it shall be lawful for the Geological`
  line `Survey of India or the specified authority or agency, and its servants and workmen--`
  line
  line `(a) to enter upon such land,`
  line
  line `(b) to dig or bore into the sub-soil,`
  line
  line `(c) to do all other acts necessary to determine the extent of any mineral available in or under`
  line `such land,`
  line
  line `(d) to set out boundaries of the land in which any mineral is expected to be found,`
  line
  line `(e) to mark such boundaries and line by placing marks,`
  line
  line `(f) where otherwise the survey cannot be completed on the boundaries and line marked, to cut`
  line `down and clear away any part of any standing crop, fence or jungle:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such authority or agency shall enter into any building or upon any enclosed court or`
  line `garden attached to a dwelling-house (except with the consent of the occupier thereof) without previously`
  line `giving such occupier at least seven days notice in writing of its intention to do so.`
  line
  line `(3) Whenever any action of the nature specified in sub-section (2) is to be taken, the Central`
  line `Government shall, before or at the time when such action is taken, pay or tender payment for all`
  line `necessary damage which is likely to be caused, and in case of dispute as to the sufficiency of the amount`
  line `so paid or tendered or as to the person to whom it should be paid or tendered, the Central Government`
  line `shall refer the dispute to the principal civil court of original jurisdiction having jurisdiction over the land`
  line `in question.`
  line
  line `(4) The fact that there exists any such dispute as is referred to in sub-section (3) shall not be a bar to`
  line `the taking of any action under sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(5) After the completion of the investigation, the Geological Survey of India or the specified`
  line `authority or agency by which the investigation was made shall submit to the Central Government a`
  line `detailed report indicating therein the extent and nature of any mineral which lies deposited in or under`
  line `the land.`
  line
  line `(6) The costs of the investigation made under this section shall be borne by the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the State Government or other person in whom the minerals are vested or the`
  line `holder of any prospecting licence ^2[or exploration licence] or mining lease applies to the Central`
  line `Government to furnish to it or him a copy of the report submitted under sub-section (5), that State`
  line `Government or other person or the holder of a prospecting licence ^2[or exploration licence] or mining`
  line `lease, as the case may be, shall bear such reasonable part of the costs of investigation as the Central`
  line `Government may specify in this behalf and shall, on payment of such part of the costs of investigation,`
  line `be entitled to receive from the Central Government a true copy of the report submitted to it under subsection (5).]`
obj_root_law_sections_18_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 56 of 1972, s. 11 (w.e.f. 12-9-1972).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 16 of 2023, s. 16 (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_18_b:
  sectionId (100320)
  sectionNo 18B
  orderNo 41
  title `Development of market.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 28 of 2025, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-9-2025).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=100320&sectionno=18B&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_18_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[18B. Development of market.--- (1) The Central Government shall endeavour to promote`
  line `development of market, including trading, of minerals, its concentrate or its processed forms (including`
  line `metals) through mineral exchanges in such manner as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint any authority to`
  line `register and regulate mineral exchanges.`
  line
  line `(3) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) registration of mineral exchanges and revocation of such registration;`
  line
  line `(b) regulation of all aspects and activities of mineral exchanges and market oversight;`
  line
  line `(c) levy of fees and other charges;`
  line
  line `(d) maintenance of a data bank of information on activities relating to mineral trading on mineral`
  line exchanges;
  line
  line `(e) prevention of cartelization, insider trading, circular trading, market manipulation and any other`
  line `matter which is detrimental to the participants of the mineral exchanges;`
  line
  line `(f) grievance redressal of participants of mineral exchanges; and`
  line
  line `(g) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (9982)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 42
  title `Mineral concession to be void if in contravention of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9982&sectionno=19&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `19. ^1[Mineral concession to be void if in contravention of Act.]--- Any ^2[mineral concession] granted,`
  line `renewed or acquired in contravention of the provisions of this Act or any rules or orders made thereunder`
  line `shall be void and of no effect.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- Where a person has acquired more than one ^2[mineral concession] ^3*** and the`
  line `aggregate area covered by such ^4[permits, licences or leases], as the case may be, exceeds the maximum`
  line `area permissible under section 6, only that ^2[mineral concession] the acquisition of which has resulted in`
  line `such maximum area being exceeded shall be deemed to be void.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 16 of 2023 s. 17, for the marginal heading (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 16 of 2021, s. 2, "reconnaissance permit, prospecting licence or mining lease" (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line
  line `3. The words "in any State" omitted by Act 25 of 1994, s. 8 (w.e.f. 25-1-1994).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 38 of 1999, s. 16, for "licences or leases" (w.e.f. 18-12-1999).`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (9983)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 43
  title `Act and rules to apply to all renewals of prospecting licences and mining leases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9983&sectionno=20&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line The
  line `provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder shall apply in relation to the renewal after the`
  line `commencement of this Act of any prospecting licence or mining lease granted before such`
  line `commencement as they apply in relation to the renewal of a prospecting licence or mining lease granted`
  line `after such commencement.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20_a:
  sectionId (9984)
  sectionNo 20A
  orderNo 44
  title `Power of Central Government to issue directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2015, s. 18 (w.e.f. 12-1-2015).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9984&sectionno=20A&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_20_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[20A. Power of Central Government to issue directions.--(1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in this Act, the Central Government may issue such directions to the State Governments, as`
  line `may be required for the conservation of mineral resources, or on any policy matter in the national`
  line `interest, and for the scientific and sustainable development and exploitation of mineral resources.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing powers, the Central`
  line `Government may also issue directions in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) improvement in procedure for grant of mineral concessions and to ensure co-ordination`
  line `among agencies entrusted with according statutory clearances;`
  line
  line `(ii) maintenance of internet-based databases including development and operation of a mining`
  line `tenement system;`
  line
  line `(iii) implementation and evaluation of sustainable development frameworks;`
  line
  line `(iv) reduction in waste generation and related waste management practices and promotion of`
  line `recycling of materials;`
  line
  line `(v) minimising and mitigating adverse environmental impacts particularly in respect of ground`
  line `water, air, ambient noise and land;`
  line
  line `(vi) ensuring minimal ecological disturbance, in terms of bio-diversity, flora, fauna and habitat;`
  line
  line `(vii) promoting restoration and reclamation activities so as to make optimal use of mined out`
  line `land for the benefit of the local communities; and`
  line
  line `(viii) such other matters as may be necessary for the purposes of implementation of this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (9985)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 45
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9985&sectionno=21&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Whoever contravenes the provisions of sub-section (1) or sub-section (1A) of`
  line `section 4 shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to five years and with fine`
  line `which may extend to five lakh rupees per hectare of the area.`
  line
  line `(2) Any rule made under any provision of this Act may provide that any contravention thereof shall`
  line `be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years or with fine which may`
  line `extend to five lakh rupees, or with both, and in the case of a continuing contravention, with additional`
  line `fine which may extend to fifty thousand rupees for every day during which such contravention continues`
  line `after conviction for the first such contravention.]`
  line
  line `^2[(3) Where any person trespasses into any land in contravention of the provisions of sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 4, such trespasser may be served with an order of eviction by the State Government or any`
  line `authority authorised in this behalf by that Government and the State Government or such authorised`
  line `authority may, if necessary, obtain the help of the police to evict the trespasser from the land.`
  line
  line `^3[(4) Whenever any person raises, transports or causes to be raised or transported, without any lawful`
  line `authority, any mineral from any land, and, for that purpose, uses any tool, equipment, vehicle or any`
  line `other thing, such mineral tool, equipment, vehicle or any other thing shall be liable to be seized by an`
  line `officer or authority specially empowered in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(4A) Any mineral, tool, equipment, vehicle or any other thing seized under sub-section (4), shall be`
  line `liable to be confiscated by an order of the court competent to take cognizance of the offence under`
  line `sub-section (1) and shall be disposed of in accordance with the directions of such court.]`
  line
  line `(5) Whenever any person raises, without any lawful authority, any mineral from any land, the State`
  line `Government may recover from such person the mineral so raised, or, where such mineral has already`
  line `been disposed of, the price thereof, and may also recover from such person, rent, royalty or tax, as the`
  line `case may be, for the period during which the land was occupied by such person without any lawful`
  line authority.]
  line
  line `^4[(6) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), an`
  line `offence under sub-section (1) shall be cognizable.]`
  line
  line `^5[Explanation.--- On and from the date of commencement of the Mines and Minerals (Development`
  line `and Regulation) Amendment Act, 2021 (16 of 2021), the expression "raising,transporting or causing to raise`
  line `or transport any mineral without any lawful authority" occurring in this section, shall mean raising,`
  line `transporting or causing to raise or transport any mineral by a person without prospecting licence, mining`
  line `lease or composite licence ^6[, exploration licence] or in contravention of the rules made under section`
  line 23C.]
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2015, s. 19, for sub-sections (1) and (2) (w.e.f. 12-1-2015).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 56 of 1972, s. 12 (w.e.f. 12-9-1972).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 38 of 1999, s. 17, for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 18-12-1999).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 37 of 1986, s. 16 (w.e.f. 10-2-1987).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 16 of 2021, s. 20 (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 16 of 2023, s. 18 (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (9986)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 46
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9986&sectionno=22&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `No court shall take cognizance of any offence punishable under this`
  line `Act or any rules made thereunder except upon complaint in writing made by a person authorised in this`
  line `behalf by the Central Government or the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (9987)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 47
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9987&sectionno=23&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the person committing an offence under this Act or any rules`
  line `made thereunder is a company, every person who at the time the offence was committed was in charge`
  line `of, and was responsible to the company for the conduct of the business of the company, shall be deemed`
  line `to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he exercised all`
  line `due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed with the consent or connivance of any director, manager, secretary or other officer of the`
  line `company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall be deemed to be guilty of that offence`
  line `and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of this section,---`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line
  line `(b) "director" in relation to a firm means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23_a:
  sectionId (9988)
  sectionNo 23A
  orderNo 48
  title `Compounding of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 56 of 1972, s. 13 (w.e.f. 12-9-1972).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9988&sectionno=23A&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_23_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[23A. Compounding of offences.--(1) Any offence punishable under this Act or any rule made`
  line `thereunder may, either before or after the institution of the prosecution, be compounded by the person`
  line `authorised under section 22 to make a complaint to the court with respect to that offence, on payment to`
  line `that person, for credit to the Government, of such sum as that person may specify:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of an offence punishable with fine only, no such sum shall exceed the`
  line `maximum amount of fine which may be imposed for that offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an offence is compounded under sub-section (1), no proceeding or further proceeding, as`
  line `the case may be, shall be taken against the offender in respect of the offence so compounded, and the`
  line `offender, if in custody, shall be released forthwith.]`
obj_root_law_sections_23_b:
  sectionId (9989)
  sectionNo 23B
  orderNo 49
  title `Power to search.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9989&sectionno=23B&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_23_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[23B. Power to search.--If any gazetted officer of the Central or a State Government authorised by`
  line `the Central Government ^2[or a State Government, as the case may be,] in this behalf by general or`
  line `special order has reason to believe that any mineral has been raised in contravention of the provisions of`
  line `this Act or rules made thereunder or any document or thing in relation to such mineral is secreted in any`
  line `place ^2[or vehicle], he may search for such mineral, document or thing and the provisions of section 100`
  line `of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), shall apply to every such search.]`
obj_root_law_sections_23_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 25 of 1994, s. 9 (w.e.f. 25-1-1994).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 38 of 1999, s. 18 (w.e.f. 18-12-1999).`
obj_root_law_sections_23_c:
  sectionId (9990)
  sectionNo 23C
  orderNo 50
  title `Power of State Government to make rules for preventing illegal mining, transportation and storage of minerals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 38 of 1999, s. 19 (w.e.f. 18-12-1999).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9990&sectionno=23C&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_23_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[23C. Power of State Government to make rules for preventing illegal mining, transportation`
  line `and storage of minerals.--- (1) The State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make`
  line `rules for preventing illegal mining, transportation and storage of minerals and for the purposes connected`
  line therewith.
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) establishment of check-posts for checking of minerals under transit;`
  line
  line `(b) establishment of weigh-bridges to measure the quantity of mineral being transported;`
  line
  line `(c) regulation of mineral being transported from the area granted under a prospecting licence or a`
  line `mining lease or a quarrying licence or a permit, in whatever name the permission to excavate`
  line `minerals, has been given;`
  line
  line `(d) inspection, checking and search of minerals at the place of excavation or storage or during`
  line transit;
  line
  line `(e) maintenance of registers and forms for the purposes of these rules;`
  line
  line `(f) the period within which and the authority to which applications for revision of any order`
  line `passed by any authority be preferred under any rule made under this section and the fees to be paid`
  line `therefor and powers of such authority for disposing of such applications; and`
  line
  line `(g) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed for the purpose of prevention`
  line `of illegal mining, transportation and storage of minerals.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 30, the Central Government shall have no power`
  line `to revise any order passed by a State Government or any of its authorised officers or any authority under`
  line `the rules made under sub-sections (1) and (2).]`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (9991)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 51
  title `Power of entry and inspection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9991&sectionno=24&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of ascertaining the position of the`
  line `working, actual or prospective, of any mine or abandoned mine or for any other purpose connected with`
  line `this Act or the rules made thereunder, any person authorised by the ^1[Central Government or a State`
  line `Government] in this behalf, by general ^2*** order, may--`
  line
  line `(a) enter and inspect any mine;`
  line
  line `(b) survey and take measurements in any such mine;`
  line
  line `(c) weigh, measure or take measurements of the stocks of minerals lying at any mine;`
  line
  line `(d) examine any document, book, register, or record in the possession or power of any person`
  line `having the control of, or connected with, any mine and place marks of identification thereon, and`
  line `take extracts from or make copies of such document, book, register or record;`
  line
  line `(e) order the production of any such document, book, register, record, as is referred to in`
  line `clause (d); and`
  line
  line `(f) examine any person having the control of, or connected with, any mine.`
  line
  line `(2) Every person authorised by the ^1[Central Government or a State Government] under`
  line `sub-section (1) shall be deemed to be a public servant within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian`
  line `Penal Code, and every person to whom an order or summons is issued by virtue of the powers conferred`
  line `by clause (e) or clause (f) of that sub-section shall be legally bound to comply with such order or`
  line `summons, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 1999, s. 20, for "Central Government" (w.e.f. 18-12-1999).`
  line
  line `2. The words "or special" omitted by s. 20, ibid. (w.e.f. 18-12-1999).`
obj_root_law_sections_24_a:
  sectionId (9992)
  sectionNo 24A
  orderNo 52
  title `Rights and liabilities of a holder of prospecting licence or mining lease.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9992&sectionno=24A&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_24_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[24A. ^2[Rights and liabilities of a holder of mineral concession.]--- (1) On the issue of a ^3[mineral`
  line `concession] under this Act and the rules made thereunder, it shall be lawful for the ^4[holder of such`
  line `permit, licence or lease], his agents or his servants or workmen to enter the lands over which ^5[such`
  line `permit, lease or licence had been granted] at all times during its currency and carry out all such`
  line `^6[reconnaissance, prospecting or mining operations] as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person shall enter into any building or upon an enclosed court or garden attached to`
  line `a dwelling-house (except with the consent of the occupier thereof) without previously giving such`
  line `occupier at least seven days' notice in writing of his intention to do so.`
  line
  line `(2) The holder of a ^3[mineral concession] referred to in sub-section (1) shall be liable to pay`
  line `compensation in such manner as may be prescribed to the occupier of the surface of the land granted`
  line `under ^7[such permit, licence or lease] for any loss or damage which is likely to arise or has arisen from or`
  line `in consequence of the ^8[reconnaissance, mining or prospecting operations].`
  line
  line `(3) The amount of compensation payable under sub-section (2) shall be determined by the State`
  line `Government in the manner prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_24_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 37 of 1986, s. 17 (w.e.f. 10-2-1987).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 16 of 2023, s. 19, for the marginal heading (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 16 of 2021, s. 2, for "reconnaissance permit, prospecting licence or mining lease" (w.e.f. 28-3-3021).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 38 of 1999, s. 21, for "holder of such licence or lease" (w.e.f. 18-12-1999).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 21, ibid., for "such lease or licence had been granted" (w.e.f. 18-12-1999).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 21, ibid., for "prospecting or mining operations" (w.e.f. 18-12-1999).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by s. 21, ibid., for "such licence or lease" (w.e.f. 18-12-1999).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by s. 21, ibid., for "mining or prospecting operations" (w.e.f. 18-12-1999).`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (9993)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 53
  title `Recovery of certain sums as arrears of land revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9993&sectionno=25&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] Any rent, royalty, tax, fee or`
  line `other sum due to the Government under this Act or the rules made thereunder or under the terms and`
  line `conditions of any ^2[mineral concession] may, on a certificate of such officer as may be specified by the`
  line `State Government in this behalf by general or special order, be recovered in the same manner as an`
  line `arrear of land revenue.`
  line
  line `^3[(2) Any rent, royalty, tax, fee or other sum due to the Government either under this Act or any rule`
  line `made thereunder or under the terms and conditions of any ^2[mineral concession] may, on a certificate of`
  line `such officer as may be specified by the State Government in this behalf by general or special order, be`
  line `recovered in the same manner as if it were an arrear of land revenue and every such sum which becomes`
  line `due to the Government after the commencement of the Mines and Minerals (Regulation and`
  line `Development) Amendment Act, 1972 (56 of 1972), together with the interest due thereon shall be a first`
  line `charge on the assets of the holder of the ^2[mineral concession], as the case may be.]`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. S. 25 re-numbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 56 of 1972, s. 14 (w.e.f. 12-9-1972).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 16 of 2021, s. 2, for "reconnaissance permit, prospecting license or mining lease" (w.e.f. 28-3-3021).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 56 of 1972, s. 14, (w.e.f. 12-9-1972)..`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (9994)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 54
  title `Delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9994&sectionno=26&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, direct that any power exercisable by it under this Act may, in relation to such matters and`
  line `subject to such conditions, if any, as may be specified in the notification be exercisable also by--`
  line
  line `(a) such officer or authority subordinate to the Central Government; or`
  line
  line `(b) such State Government or such officer or authority subordinate to a State Government, as`
  line `may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct that any power`
  line `exercisable by it under this Act may, in relation to such matters and subject to such conditions, if any, as`
  line `may be specified in the notification, be exercisable also by such officer or authority subordinate to the`
  line `State Government as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(3) Any rules made by the Central Government under this Act may confer powers and impose duties`
  line `or authorise the conferring of powers and imposition of duties upon any State Government or any officer`
  line `or authority subordinate thereto.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (9995)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 55
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9995&sectionno=27&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceedings shall`
  line `lie against any person for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (9996)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 56
  title `Rules and notifications to be laid before Parliament and certain rules to be approved by Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9996&sectionno=28&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Every rule and every notification made by the Central Government under this Act`
  line `shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament while it is in session`
  line `for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive`
  line `sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive`
  line `sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or notification or both`
  line `Houses agree that the rule or notification should not be made, the rule or notification shall thereafter`
  line `have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `that rule or notification.]`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the rule making power vested in the Central Government,`
  line `no rules made with reference to clause (c) of sub-section (2) of section 16 shall come into force until`
  line `they have been approved, whether with or without modifications, by each House of Parliament.`
  line
  line `^2[(3) Every rule and every notification made by the State Government under this Act shall be laid, as`
  line `soon as may be after it is made, before each House of the State Legislature where it consists of two`
  line `Houses, or where such Legislature consists one House, before that House.]`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 56 of 1972, s. 15, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 12-9-1972).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 25 of 1994, s. 10 (w.e.f. 25-1-1994)`
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (9997)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 57
  title `Existing rules to continue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9997&sectionno=29&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `All rules made or purporting to have been made under the Mines`
  line `and Minerals (Regulation and Development) Act, 1948 (53 of 1948), shall, insofar as they relate to`
  line `matters for which provision is made in this Act and are not inconsistent therewith, be deemed to have`
  line `been made under this Act as if this Act had been in force on the date on which such rules were made and`
  line `shall continue in force unless and until they are superseded by any rules made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (9998)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 58
  title `Power of revision by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2015, s. 20, for section 30 (w.e.f. 12-1-2015).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9998&sectionno=30&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `^1[30. Power of revision by Central Government.--- The Central Government may, of its own`
  line `motion or on an application made within the prescribed time by an aggrieved party,---`
  line
  line `(a) revise any order made by a State Government or other authority in exercise of the powers`
  line `conferred on it by or under this Act with respect to any mineral other than a minor mineral; or`
  line
  line `(b) where no such order has been made by the State Government or other authority in exercise of`
  line `the powers conferred on it by or under this Act with respect to any mineral other than a minor`
  line `mineral within the time prescribed therefore, pass such order as it may think fit and appropriate in`
  line `the circumstances:`
  line
  line `Provided that in cases covered by clause (b) the Central Government shall, before passing any`
  line `order under this clause, give an opportunity of being heard or to represent in the matter.]`
obj_root_law_sections_30_a:
  sectionId (9999)
  sectionNo 30A
  orderNo 59
  title `Special provisions relating to mining leases for coal granted before 25th October, 1949.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 1958, s. 2 (w.e.f. 15-5-1958).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=9999&sectionno=30A&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_30_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[30A. Special provisions relating to mining leases for coal granted before 25th October,`
  line `1949.--- Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the provisions of sub-section (1) of section 9`
  line `and sub-section (1) of section 16 shall not apply to or in relation to mining leases granted before the 25th`
  line `day of October, 1949, in respect of coal, but the Central Government, if it is satisfied that it is expedient`
  line `so to do, may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct that all or any of the said provisions`
  line `(including any rules made under sections 13 and 18) shall apply to or in relation to such leases subject to`
  line `such exceptions and modifications, if any, as may be specified in that or in any subsequent notification.]`
obj_root_law_sections_30_b:
  sectionId (10000)
  sectionNo 30B
  orderNo 60
  title `Constitution of Special Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2015, s. 21 (w.e.f. 12-1-2015).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=10000&sectionno=30B&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_30_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[30B. Constitution of Special Courts.--- (1) The State Government may, for the purposes of`
  line `providing speedy trial of offences for contravention of the provisions of sub-section (1) or`
  line `sub-section (1A) of section 4, constitute, by notification, as many Special Courts as may be necessary for`
  line `such area or areas, as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) A Special Court shall consist of a Judge who shall be appointed by the State Government with`
  line `the concurrence of the High Court.`
  line
  line `(3) A person shall not be qualified for appointment as a judge of a Special Court unless he is or has`
  line `been a District and Sessions Judge.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person aggrieved by the order of the Special Court may prefer an appeal to the High Court`
  line `within a period of sixty days from the date of such order.]`
obj_root_law_sections_30_c:
  sectionId (10001)
  sectionNo 30C
  orderNo 61
  title `Special Courts to have powers of Court of Session.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2015, s. 21 (w.e.f. 12-1-2015).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=10001&sectionno=30C&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_30_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[30C. Special Courts to have powers of Court of Session.--- Save as otherwise provided in this Act,`
  line `the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), shall apply to the proceedings before the Special`
  line `Court and for the purpose of the provisions of this Act, the Special Court shall be deemed to be a Court`
  line `of Session and shall have all powers of a Court of Session and the person conducting a prosecution`
  line `before the Special Court shall be deemed to be a public prosecutor.]`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (10002)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 62
  title `Relaxation of rules in special cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 16 of 2021, s. 2, "reconnaissance permit, prospecting licence or mining lease" (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=10002&sectionno=31&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, if it is of opinion that in`
  line `the interests of mineral development it is necessary so to do, by order in writing and for reasons to be`
  line `recorded, authorise in any case the grant, renewal or transfer of any ^1[mineral concession], or the`
  line `working of any mine for the purpose of searching for or winning any mineral, on terms and conditions`
  line `different from those laid down in the rules made under section 13.`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (10003)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 63
  title [Repealed].
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=10003&sectionno=32&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `[Amendments to Act 53 of 1948].--Rep. by the Repealing and Amending Act, 1960 (58 of 1960),`
  line `s. 2 and the First Schedule (w.e.f. 26-12-1960).`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (12964)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 64
  title `Validation of certain acts and indemnity`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197&sectionId=12964&sectionno=33&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00002_195767_1517807322197
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `All acts of executive authority done, proceedings`
  line `taken and sentences passed under the Mines and Minerals (Regulation and Development) Act, 1948 (53`
  line `of 1948), with respect to the regulation of mines and the development of minerals during the period`
  line `commencing on the 26th day of January, 1950, and ending with the date of commencement of this Act`
  line `by the Government or by any officer of the Government or by any other authority, in the belief or`
  line `purported belief that the acts, proceedings of sentences were being done, taken or passed under the said`
  line `Act, shall be as valid and operative as if they had been done, taken or passed in accordance with law, and`
  line `no suit or other legal proceeding shall be maintained or continued against any person whatsoever, on the`
  line `ground that any such acts, proceedings or sentences were not done, taken or passed in accordance with`
  line law.
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
